Dr did check my white blood count from last week and there was no issues.  I took two Tylenol (one at 8:30 pm and one 10 pm) and went to bed. Thank you.

The day of the vaccine, I could barely move my arm. It was a completely different soreness. I had to move my right arm(one with vaccine) using my left arm. It was as if there was a bullet lodged in there-I could only move it a few degrees-and whenever I did, I would get a strong jolt of pain. The pain subsided, but never completely went away. Today it is March 21st and I received my vaccine on February 25th. I still cannot sleep on my right side. My doctor thinks it is bursitis and that the person who administered the vaccine did so in the wrong location-resulting in inflammation in the bursa of the shoulder. Additionally, we weren't seated to receive our vaccine. We received it standing up, and in my opinion, I think it is very hard to relax your arm doing that. It was an extremely quick shot-spot was cleaned, vaccine was administered, and line moved up. Pain sometimes lessens quite a bit, but if I put any pressure unknowingly in my sleep on the location, pain goes right back up. At the moment, pain is maybe 2/10. I can finally move my arm in all directions, but pain has not gone away. While I do not know for sure, I am very scared that this may be permanent.

Patient had vaccine on 3/18/21 at 1600. She presented to the ED on 3/21/21 @ 2202 for chest pain that started at ~1600. She states the chest pain is in the center of her chest, feels like pressure, non-radiating, with occasional shortness of breath. It felt similar to when she had COVID in January. She denies other symptoms including fever, URI symptoms, palpitations, pain with deep inspiration, leg swelling, recent travel, nausea/vomiting, diarrhea, dizziness, feeling like she was going to pass out, rash or other symptoms. It is not exertional and was better with walking. Denies heavy lifting or injury. She was hypertensive in the ED BP 151/99 but all other vitals within normal limits. EKG shows NSR without evidence of arrhythmia or ischemic changes. She did have U waves seen so labs were drawn including CBC, CMP, cardiac enzymes. Chest x-ray showed no acute cardiopulmonary process. She received 30 mg Toradol IV for pain. Labs were all within normal limits except mild hypokalemia. She felt better on reassessment and BP was still elevated but improved 137/90. She was discharged and instructed to take OTC Tylenol as on the bottle as needed for pain and given return precautions and follow up with PCP on return to stateside.
LAB_DATA: EKG: NSR, without evidence of arrhythmia, ischemia. normal intervals, normal axis, no ST segment or T wave abnormalities. Positive U wave.   CXR: No acute cardiopulmonary process  Labs: CBC wnl. CMP wnl except mild hypokalemia, cardiac enzymes negative including troponin, CK-MB and myoglobin

At approximately 10:35am client had completed his 15mins observation and was ready to go home when he briefly felt his throat closing. He then called 911 and went back inside to EMT station and notified EMTs. He was then assessed and denied history of Anaphylaxis or allergies to food or meds. Assessment revealed no hives, rashes, skin flare ups, itchiness or shortness of breath. Client denied chest pain, difficulty breathing or pain throughout the body. Initial  Vital signs were taken and taken every 5mins after that. He was asked to stay for 30mins. Client told 911 operator he felt safe to hang up and stay with EMT at vaccination site. Client's initial vital signs were a pulse of 112, Blood pressure of 164/92, O2 sat of 99% on room air and respirations of 24 with no signs of accessory muscle use. Due to client's vitals improving with his calmer demeanor, no additional interventions were felt to be necessary at this time. Client stated he felt better and was encouraged to follow up with his Primary Care Provider and emergency precautions were given. Numbness in lower lip and numbness and slight trembling in right side of face (similar to Bells Palsy?) after four days of being administered the first shot in the right arm. After a video consult with my PCP it was recommended that I go to the hospital and get a CT scan to rule out a possible minor stroke. The CT scan was negative. The numbness became better after two weeks but has not subsided.  After consultation with the doctor in charge of the vaccine operation for the site it was decided that I go ahead and take the second shot but instead of the right arm I should take it in either the left arm or the left thigh. The second shot was administered in the left thigh. I experienced the typical symptoms on the second day - fever, chills and aches and pain but they went away towards the end of the second day. However, exactly on the fourth day I experienced increased numbness in my lower lip and on the right side of my face. Today is the fifth day and it is still there. I expect that this numbness will continue for several weeks as it did with the first shot and so far it has not subsided after the first shot and has now increased after the second shot. I am totally convinced that this is a direct result of the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: CT scan was performed at the hospital to rune out a possible mild stroke and was found to be negative.

Pt received the Janssen Covid-19 vaccine. Pt started to feel numbness and tingling in his left hand (vaccinated arm) 15 minutes following the immunization. Pt stated that he felt fine other than his left hand experiencing numbness and tingling, specifically in his fingertips. Pt had no other adverse symptoms. I asked the pt to remain seated for an additional 15 minutes. He stated that he was ok but I convinced him to remain in his seat so we could continue to evaluate him. After a total of 45 minutes of evaluation, pt stated that the feeling of numbness and tingling was gone. Once again, I verified with the pt that he was feeling ok, with no additional adverse feeling or symptoms. Pt stated that he felt fine now and only felt a little soreness at the injection site.

I don't think that my reaction to the vaccine is super serious but it is perhaps worth noting if others are also experiencing similar symptoms. On the second day, I did have the expected arm soreness around the injection area on my right arm. That soreness faded by Saturday morning. However, on Saturday afternoon, I began experiencing some intermittent pain in my left kidney. I have had a few (3?) kidney stones since I was approximately 35 years old so it is a pain that I recognize almost immediately.  I kept my spider senses awake to see where it was going to go. About an hour later, I had intermittent "flu like" pain in my arms and legs. I had been up on a ladder painting a wall and I became a bit dizzy and decided to halt the painting project. The rest of the evening was kind of crappy. Intermittent headaches, leg pain, arm pain and left kidney pain. I took 1 Alleve tablet around 8pm. It didn't seem to do much. I took a second one about an hour later (according to the instructions you can take two for you first dose) and that seemed to do the trick! I slept like a rock and so far today, all of the pain is gone including the pain in my left kidney.  I have not taken any more Alleve besides the two that I took last night. Also, as of right now (2:44pm on Sunday 3/21), no kidney stone has passed. I have been urinating into a cup to see if one comes out. I cannot 100% say that any of these symptoms are related to the vaccine. However, being a Type 1 diabetic (since 1978) and the unusual kidney pain made me go, "huh." That is why I am providing this info in the event that there are others who are experiencing similar symptoms that can be tied to the vaccine and what to expect. I feel completely fine now. Yay. :)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Nine minutes after receiving the vaccine, I began to feel "weird", then hot.  I asked the nurse to take my temperature, but it was normal. They called EMTs who took my blood pressure -it was 166 over about 82.  They gave me oxygen and took me to the hospital.  I was incredibly thirsty and drank a huge glass of ice water.   After being monitored and released within about  2 hours, I felt brain fog.  The brain fog worsened the next day and significantly worsened on the second day after the vaccine.  It was so bad that it felt like having a concussion:  I had trouble word-finding and was stumbling all over my words.  The night of the vaccine, I had hot flashes all night long.  Eight days after the vaccine, I developed "COVID-arm".

1310-Went to the Observation area as a patient was not feeling well, after her 2nd pfizer vaccine, to the left arm.  Medical personnel and I went to the patient and she was sitting in a chair in the 30 min area and she had altered level of conscious. The patient stated she started not feeling well, had some chest pressure and felt she was going to pass out. We stayed with the patient, Vitals signs 149/87 HR 89, pulse ox 98% respiratory 12 Lungs clear in all fields. Patient denied any shortness of breath, and denied any swelling of her throat or tongue. I advised the patient to focus on her breathing and if this had happen before and she stated yes, the patient identified that she is allergic to the influenza shot and yellow fever and this happened when she had those injections, and she was ok after a few minutes. I asked the patient if she had any of these symptoms with the first Pfizer injection and she stated yes, but very little and didn't say anything to anyone during the first injection. We continued to stay with the patient. The patient never losses consciousness, however it appears to be decrease as she was speaking slowly and moving her arms slowly, then the patient start to cry and could answer the questions normally. I asked if the patient was alone or if someone was with her and she stated her husband.  I asked the patient to please call her husband and she did. Other medical personnel remained with the patient and I went to the front and found the husband. While I took the husband to the patient she started to have decease level of conscious and we took the patient's vital signs again. 1321- 130/88, HR 77, pulse Ox 96% respiratory rate 14. I continued to talk with the patient and the patient level of conscious returned. The patient stated she had some chest pressure and this was her normal to the reaction, she started to cry again. I continued to comfort the patient and we spoke and the patient identified that she had this reaction with anesthesia before, also dental work, and also with Demerol. I advised the patient to please reach out to her primary physician right away, to discuss the reaction that she is encountering as they maybe able to find out what her body is reacting to and she verbalized understanding. The patient remained in observation and was communication normally. at 1328 vitals signs were completed 133/85, HR 78, pulse ox 96%, respiratory rate 14. Other medical personnel and I continued to monitor the patient and at 1344 vitals signs completed 142/87, HR 70 pulse ox 98% respiratory rate 14. Patient stated she was much better and felt good to go home to eat something and the patient was sent home with her husband.
ALLERGIES: Influenza Vaccine Yellow Fever Anesthesia  Dental Work  Demerol

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my first Pfizer shot on March 3rd. No reactions at all. About 13 days later on Tuesday, March 15th, I noticed a small rash on my right side upper eye lid and the side of my eye but thought it may just be an allergic reaction to something. No pain or itching. I had a couple of similar spots on my scalp but didn?t think much of it. On Thursday, I had a headache but I do get headaches now and then. When I woke up on Friday morning, March 19th, I found my eye lid completely swollen and saw the rash had turned to blisters, and there was a new one by the inner corner of my eye and a very faint rash on my forehead. Still no fever, pain or fatigue but had a lingering headache and a burning sensation on the rash. Saw my opthalmologist right away who diagnosed it as shingles and did a complete eye exam. Luckily no shingles in the eye as that can lead to glaucoma or even blindness in severe cases. I was prescribed Valtrex (1000 mg x 7 days) and prednisone (60 mg x 5 days) by my PCP. Hoping that I was still in the 72 hour window when the antiviral med is effective, I started on the meds immediately. Today is the third day of treatment and the blisters seem to be crusting away and healing faster. Luckily, no new blisters as of now. The prednisone caused my eye area to swell up further so I am gradually tapering off the dosage from 60 mg prescribed to 40-30-20 mg.  Keeping a watch for any complications such as ear pain or numbness in the face. Have a follow up appointment with ophthalmologist who will be dilating my eyes for further checks. I was glad to have found the Reddit board and see that there are over 50 cases of people reporting shingles after the first or second covid vaccine. I plan to delay or skip my second Pfizer vaccine for now.
LAB_DATA: Eye exam by optometrist on March 19th, 2021. Eyes normal.  Eye exam and shingles diagnosis by Opthalmologist on March 19, 2021. Eyes normal. Follow up eye exam on Tuesday, March 23, 2021

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1 day after receiving the 2nd Moderna shot I began to experience severe nausea & vomiting precipitated by intense vertigo. The vertigo was so severe that I had visual disturbances, severe headaches, loss of balance, poor concentration including memory problems, and ringing in the ears that precluded these attacks. These events occurred 1-2 times a day. It has devastated my life.  These episodes take 1-3 hours to overcome and their is no specific time of day they happen. I had to be hospitalized for 2 days exactly 1 week post vaccination. The healthcare providers can not agree that these events are directly caused by this vaccine. I've been told it's central nervous inflammation caused by my immune system over reacting from the vaccine. I have no history of vertigo or really migraine headaches. The neurologists say these symptoms are vestibular migraines or vestibular vertigo (positional).  It's now almost 3 months and I'm still struggling with these symptoms but thankfully not as severe and debilitating.  Shot 1/27/21, first day of symptoms 1/28 and hospitalized 2/3 to 2/5.
LAB_DATA: CT scan/MRI with contrast. Lab work 2/3 -2/5

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Mast cell disease; Shortness of breath; Dizziness; Palpitations; Vertigo; Allergic reaction; Weird feeling; Pruritus; This spontaneous case was received on 12-Mar-2021 from other non-health professional via Med Communication (reference number: SEQW21-00979) and concerned female patient of an unknown age.  The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported.   On 27-Oct-2018, the patient was vaccinated with Flucelvax Quadrivalent (influenza vaccine, subunit influenza virus vaccine polyvalent; dose: 0.5 ml; route of administration and anatomical location: not reported) for prevention of seasonal influenza. The batch number reported was 252674 and expiry date was 30-Jun-2019.  On the same day, after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent, the patient had had an allergic reaction. She experienced shortness of breath, dizziness, palpitations and also vertigo, 'a weird feeling' and pruritus.   On an unknown date in 2018, the patient was treated with Benadryl (diphenhydramine hydrochloride) and 'some other stuff'. It was reported that the patient was not hospitalized.   On an unspecified date, all of these things caused mast cell disease as reported.  The outcome of the events was not reported.  The reporter did not provide a causality assessment.  The event of 'mast cell activation syndrome' was considered to be medically significant by a Physician.  Company comment: A patient of unreported age was vaccinated with Flucelvax Quadrivalent. On the same day, after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent, the patient experienced allergic reaction, dyspnoea, dizziness, palpitations, vertigo, a weird feeling (Feeling abnormal) and pruritus. On an unspecified date, these events caused mast cell disease as reported. Causal role of the suspect vaccine is assessed as possibly related for all events. Per Brighton collaboration criteria, presented information correspond to level 3 diagnostic certainty for anaphylaxis.; Sender's Comments: A patient of unreported age was vaccinated with Flucelvax Quadrivalent. 8.5 hours after vaccine injection, I suddenly began experiencing fatigue and extreme joint and muscle soreness.   Initially I noticed my knees hurting with radiating pain up into my thighs.  My head hurt, particularly at the back of my skull, near my neck.  My neck muscles were sore, as were BOTH shoulders - my right shoulder (injection site) was only slightly sorer than my left shoulder.  I called a 24/7 nurse associated with insurance company to ask if ibuprofen or tylenol were acceptable treatments for my symptoms.  She told me I could take either and alternate if I felt I needed to maximize relief.  I noticed the joins in my toes and fingers were hurting.  It was frightening to experience tightness in my chest and back muscles.  I never felt like my lungs were compromised, there was just a heaviness as the muscles seemed constricted.  I felt a slight rise in my heart rate and experienced a few palpitations mostly because I kept pondering how much worse my symptoms could get.  I was a little cold, so I decided to go to bed after drinking extra water (also a suggestion from the nurse).  I slept for a few hours 10:00 PM - 4:00 AM then got up and called an advise nurse to report that my joint and muscle pain were not subsiding.  She encouraged water and more painkiller.  As the day wore on, I felt less achy and more shaky/jittery.  My thinking was somewhat unclear - I felt a little dizzy, out of balance, off-kilter and brain "foggy."  As I write this 36 hours after my injection, my symptoms are subsiding.  Where I felt a little chilled during our cool and rainy afternoon, I now feel a wave of heat sort of traveling through my body.  It isn't a fever - just an odd sensation that something is still going on.
LAB_DATA: None, yet.  I was encouraged by the nurses I contacted to give myself 72 hours if my symptoms did not get worse before contacting a doctor.  I wonder if I should receive the second shot or not.  I do not want to have a reaction that is any stronger or worse than what I have already experienced.
HISTORY: osteopenia. one kidney stone 10 years ago

However, approximately 2.5 weeks post 2nd vaccination I began to experience peripheral neuropathic symptoms  on the dorsal surfaces of bilateral hands (C6-7 dermatomes). It felt as if I were in a shower with a fine mist hitting both hands - even though the hands themselves were completely dry!. Only occurred while outdoors walking. No pain/numbness/weakness. Lasted roughly 10 days, starting to abate over last 48 hours! Coincidentally, had my first haircut (professional) in a year 3 days ago. I mentioned that it felt good to get out now that I was fully vaccinated. Without suggestion, the hair cutter mentioned that her 81-82 year old mother had had a 2nd vaccination and started feeling ?bugs crawling on the backs of her hands.? My eyes were like saucers because this was a totally-unsolicited remark which closely mimicked the symptoms I was experiencing. Fortunately, they seem to be resolving....!
OTHER_MEDS: Zyrtec, Singulair, FloNase, Rosuvastatin, Tamsulosin, MVI, Vit.C, Melatonin, ASA 81 mg
HISTORY: Hypercholesterolemia, BPH, mild GERD, perennial allergic rhinitis
PRIOR_VAX: Anaphylaxis S/P allergy desensitization injections (*2; remote)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Had localized itch on back prior to vaccine. Within days or at most a couple weeks of receiving the second dose of my vaccine I started to have symptomatic dermatographia with scratching that manifested as follicular urticaria. This became more widespread where ever I was itchy and scratched. Im being treated with antihistamines and it is improving but not resolved.

Starting two days after shot was exhausted, taking naps every day which is highly unusual and has never happened to me after any vaccination. Six days after the vaccine I woke up with a medium level fever (101.5) and spent the next 24 hours unable to keep down food or even liquids. When I drank one gulp of water with Tylenol, I would vomit it back up. Six times in one day. Fever reduced to 100 by evening but still  feeling very unwell . Hopefully it subsides by tomorrow

Guillain-Barre syndrome; This is a literature case initially received on 06-Jan-2020, concerning 67-year-old, male patient.   The literature citation:One in a million: Guillain-Barre syndrome.  The patient's medical history included hypertension, hyperlipidaemia, emphysema, and gastroesophageal reflux disease. Patient did not have recent respiratory or gastrointestinal infections, surgery, trauma, HIV, or constitutional symptoms.  The patient's concomitant medications were not reported.  On an unknown date, the patient was administered INN Flu Vaccine Seasonal [influenza virus vaccine polyvalent; dose, route of administration and anatomical location, batch number, and expiry date: not reported] for an unknown indication.   On an unknown date the patient presented with complaints of abdominal distention and tingling sensation of both hands and feet.   On the next days, two weeks after vaccination, the patient was admitted to a hospital.   After admission the initial physical examination was unremarkable for diminished motor strength in upper (3/5) and lower extremities (2/5) accompanied by areflexia.   On an unknown date, during hospitalization the patient's condition worsened with subsequent development of ataxia as well as generalized weakness.  Thirty-six hours after admission, the patient developed respiratory muscle weakness with worsening negative inspiratory force (NIF) and subsequent hypercapnic respiratory failure requiring endotracheal intubation.  On an unknown date, the patient underwent laboratory evaluation which was unremarkable and head computerised tomography (CT) scan which did not suggest acute intracranial event.   The patient also underwent cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) analysis which failed to reveal albuminocytologic dissociation or any acute infectious process and electromyography to evaluate for polyneuropathy revealed delayed distal latencies, decreased velocity, and absent F waves suggestive of an acute demyelinating polyneuropathy.  This case was recognized as Guillain-Barre syndrome, potential complication of influenza vaccine.   On an unknown date, the patient was treated with intravenous immunoglobulins (IVIGs) for 5 days, but he did not wean from mechanical ventilation, so tracheostomy was performed, along with a percutaneous endoscopic gastrostomy due to dysphagia.   The patient also had two additional courses of IVIGs and one course of plasmapheresis were administered which led to weaning of mechanical ventilation and improvement of motor function.   On an unknown date the patient was discharged on physical rehabilitation and was recovering from the event.   Per company, the event of Guillain-Barre syndrome was assessed as serious due to the criterion of medical significance and hospitalisation.  The reporter considered the event of Guillain-Barre syndrome as related to INN Flu Vaccine Seasonal.  Company comment: The patient experienced Guillain-Barre syndrome after vaccination with the suspect product, INN Flu Vaccine Seasonal. Chronology is plausible. No concomitant medications were provided. Considering all the above mentioned, causality between suspect product and the event is assessed as related.; Sender's Comments: The patient experienced Guillain-Barre syndrome after vaccination with the suspect product, INN Flu Vaccine Seasonal. Chronology is plausible. No concomitant medications were provided. Considering all the above mentioned, causality between suspect product and the event is assessed as related.

Action taken with second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to events was unknown. Most prominent region was to the most lateral region of my axillary area with pain that has been sharp and radiating. Cultures are pending. Patient's received 2nd dose of Moderna vaccine Friday 3/12.  Her husband reported she had not unexpected fatigue,  malaise, and fever for 1 day but better after that.  On Monday she began complaining of shortness of breath.  This progressively worsened and she started having presyncopal episodes.  On Saturday she was unable to come down the stairs in the house so husband planned to take her to the hospital but she stood up and passed out and woke up quickly.  He decided to call EMS.  By the time she presented to our hospital she was cyanotic and agonal breathing.  On moving her from EMS stretcher to ED bed she had PEA cardiac arrest.  She underwent mechanical device CPR with only brief (<1 min) ROSC x1.  She at some point did have a shockable rhythm.  Cath lab was notified and she was taken emergently to the cath lab with ongoing mechanical device CPR.  Peripheral VA ECMO was placed after about 1.5 hours.  Pulmonary angiogram was done which showed massive saddle PE with near complete obliteration of the right pulmonary tree and some filling defects in the left tree as well.  At that time she had severe mixed respiratory and metabolic acidosis with a lactate of 24.  She also had no gag or corneal reflex, minimally responsive pupils, and no response to noxious stimuli.  Mechanical thrombectomy was attempted with some result.  She was transferred to the SICU with increasing pressor requirement, and DIC.  Ultimately, the venous catheter of the ECMO circuit malfunctioned thought to be secondary propagating IVC thrombosis.  Family decided to withdraw care and she passed away.
OTHER_MEDS: Xulane birth control patch  Prescribed prednisone the day prior to presentation

My husband had a stroke one week after his 2nd dose. The blood clot affected his occipital lobe. Ten years ago he had a stroke in the same area below this area. On that Monday around 7 PM, he took our refuse out to the curb in front of our home. When he came in he did not recognize me or his surroundings.  I took him to the hospital by car as I was not sure what happened to him. After testing the doctors said he had a minor infarct. The stroke affected his memory. He was very confused and did not remember anything from the moment of the incident until moments before exiting the MRI machine, approximately 2 hours later. He still cannot recall anything surrounding the incident. We questioned if this was related to his recent vaccination and the doctors stated no, however, we believe it is something that should be reported since it occurred a week after the vaccination.
LAB_DATA: At our local hospital, pt he had a chest x-ray, a CAT scan of his head and neck, and an MRI. of his head showing a 2-3 mm area damaged near where a prior stroke occurred in the left occipital lobe. SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few hours after the J&J shot, I started experiencing a strong under the skin itch/stabbing sensation, which was particularly bad at the injection site and around the injected arm. I then broke out in a fever and took a 4hr nap in the middle of the day (unusual) after a normal night's sleep. Over the course of the week, I developed a migrating cold that felt like, at first,  a standard cold, a sinus infection, and, then, laryngitis as it worked its way back and got more intense and then faded. This was accompanied by breathlessness (blood oxygen levels around 90% according to finger reader), fatigue and mental impairment (disorientation, hallucinations), as well as daily fevers met with 2-6hr naps.  Basically, it felt like I picked up a really bad cold in the 3hr-1week after I got the vaccine.   This is in line with how my body has responded to the flu shot and other vaccines. For example, I've receive three flu shots and each time came down with the flu or something exactly like it 12hr-2weeks later. Those are the only times I've had the flu or something like it.
PRIOR_VAX: flu vaccines (unknown) 2007, 2008, 2009

Pathology confirmed: OXALATE NEPHROPATHY. Unclear trigger for abrupt onset of AKI requiring initiation of dialysis in this lady with hyperoxaluria. Her hyperoxaluria is thought due to roux-en-y bypass. But unclear why she abruptly had Cr go from 1.2 mg/dl in Dec 2020 to 11 on 3/10/21 with oliguria.  I - her attending hospitalist - am unsure what precipitated the crisis. I've attending renal pathology conference which discussed case. Some nephrologist entertained attributing it to Cdiff colitis, but the existing literature for this is very limited and her infection seems to have followed her AKI, rather than preceded it.   Although unlikely, I've considered that patient may have existed with supersaturate hyperoxaluric state  that experienced shock to equilibrium after small PEG injection of pfizer vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt. presented to ER on 3/19/2021. Family reports that pt. received her Covid vaccination on 3/17/2021. Since then her stomach started hurting and pt. is lethargic. Admin. 2 units of pack cells and was transported to hospital.

My left arm was mildly sore for a week, then one week after I began extreme pain in upper left arm. Nothing had changed in my left except getting the vaccine. After seeing 2 NPs and an orthopedic doctor, they advised not moving the arm if it was painful. I finally went to another orthopedic when it kept getting worse and the NP there diagnosed me with a frozen shoulder, gave me cortizone pills and prescribed physical therapy.  After over 3 weeks, it's now getting better, but still a long way from normal (pre-COVID shot). I do not think it was the shot itself; I think it was the administration of it. The Pharmacy did not give me a shot card (went back a few days and requested one), did not ask anyone to wait the 15 minutes to monitor reactions, and they did not schedule the 2nd shot at the time of the first shot. When I called to let them know I had issues with the first shot, they just said, "OK" and hung up.

Saturday night (3/13/21) and into Sunday morning (3/14/21), patient began feeling discomfort in lower right leg. Discomfort and feeling of swelling continued through Sunday evening. Monday (3/15/21) patient began using compression stocking and elevating leg, which eased some discomfort. Slight swelling, discomfort, and heat in the leg continued throughout entire week. DVT presumed. Contacted physician. Treatment for DVT and treatment dosage (Fondaparinux 7.5mg) commenced Wednesday (3/17/21) through to date. Discomfort has dissipated but slight swelling still remains. Appears to be getting better each day, although a very slow progression. Patient history of antiphospholipid syndrome has been managed for over fifteen years with blood thinners. Onset of a clotting event always followed a justifiable cause. No spontaneous/unexplainable clotting events to date. Patient otherwise healthy without any other current event which could explain a blood clot following vaccination. Reporting this information as it may be helpful in determining whether persons with APS or similar condition should receive Covid-19 vaccination. Note: this information being provided by patient.

Patient got a Covid19 (Moderna) vaccine and about 5 minutes after waiting in the wait area he felt dizzy. He attempted to get up and and fell to the floor. He was awake, alert and spoke intelligently while EMT team was being expected. After about 10 minutes he sat up on the floor and was doing just fine. SYMPTOM_TEXT: weakness/progressive generalized muscle weakness/neuromuscular weakness of unknown etiology; respiratory failure/acute hypoxic respiratory failure; recurrent aspiration; recurrent mucus plugging; pneumonia; gastrointestinal bleeding; hemorrhagic shock; hypertension; Atrial fibrillation; possibly GBS; Eaton-Lambert syndrome; myasthenia gravis; Initial information received on 13-Mar-2021 regarding an unsolicited valid serious case from a other health professional.   This case is linked to cases 2021SA091271, 2021SA091226, 2021SA091286, 2021SA091303, 2021SA091334, 2021SA091349, 2021SA091366, 2021SA091398, 2021SA091448, 2021SA091468, 2021SA091489, 2021SA091516, 2021SA091556, 2021SA091604, 2021SA091690, 2021SA091745, 2021SA091782, 2021SA091798, 2021SA091833, 2021SA091855 and 2021SA091879. (Same Literature article)  Abstract: On October 7, 2016, the Food and Drug Administration approved recombinant hemagglutinin quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4) (Spodoptera frugiperda cell line; Flublok Quadrivalent) for active immunization for the prevention of influenza disease in individuals 18 years of age and older. Clinical trials did not reveal any major differences in adverse events or serious adverse events following Flublok Quadrivalent versus standard dose quadrivalent inactivated influenza vaccine. To improve our understanding of the safety profile of this vaccine, we reviewed and summarized adverse event reports after Flublok Quadrivalent administration to the vaccine adverse event reporting system (VAERS). Through June 30, 2020, VAERS received 849 reports after RIV4 vaccination. The vast majority (810; 95%) were nonserious. Among serious events, there were 10 cases of Guillain-Barre syndrome, including 5 people who required mechanical ventilation and 2 people who died. Many allergic reactions were reported as non-serious, but required interventions to treat a life-threatening event, example: epinephrine, nebulizers, albuterol, glucocorticoids, and supplemental oxygen. Two people experienced a positive rechallenge (which are allergic reactions after repeated vaccination with RIV4), including a person who despite premedication with antihistamines developed respiratory difficulties, required epinephrine, and was transported to the emergency department. The occurrence of anaphylaxis and other allergic reactions in some individuals may reflect an underlying predisposition to atopy that may manifest itself after an exposure to any drug or vaccine and does not necessarily suggest that Flublok Quadrivalent is particularly allergenic. Post marketing safety surveillance will continue to be vital for understanding the benefits and risks of quadrivalent recombinant influenza vaccine.  This case involves a 84 year old male patient who experienced weakness/progressive generalized muscle weakness/neuromuscular weakness of unknown etiology (muscular weakness), respiratory failure/acute hypoxic respiratory failure (acute respiratory failure), recurrent aspiration (aspiration), recurrent mucus plugging (bronchial secretion retention), pneumonia, gastrointestinal bleeding (gastrointestinal haemorrhage), hypertension, atrial fibrillation, possibly GBS (Guillain-Barre syndrome) and Eaton-Lambert syndrome (myasthenic syndrome) or myasthenia gravis, after he received INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE [FLUBLOK QIV].  Past medical treatment, vaccination family history and concomitant medications were not reported.  At the time of the event, the patient had ongoing coronary artery disease.   On an unknown date, the patient received a dose of suspect INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE [lot number, expiry date and other dosing details were not reported] via an unknown route at unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination.  On an unknown date, the patient developed a serious weakness (muscular weakness) and respiratory failure (acute respiratory failure), 10 days following the administration of INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE. The patient was hospitalized for this event.  The hospital management included mechanical ventilation, intravenous immunoglobulin, and glucocorticoids as a corrective treatment to the patient.  It was reported that, patient's hospital course was complicated by pneumonia, hemorrhagic shock (shock haemorrhagic) due to gastrointestinal bleeding (gastrointestinal haemorrhage), hypertension, and atrial fibrillation. The medical records state that he had neuromuscular weakness of unknown etiology, possibly GBS (Guillain-Barre syndrome), Eaton-Lambert syndrome (myasthenic syndrome) or myasthenia gravis. (unknown latency)  The inpatient death summary listed, acute hypoxic respiratory failure with recurrent mucus plugging (bronchial secretion retention) and recurrent aspiration (aspiration) in the setting of progressive generalized muscle weakness. (unknow latency)  The pneumonia, shock haemorrhagic, gastrointestinal haemorrhage, atrial fibrillation, Guillain-Barre syndrome, myasthenic syndrome, myasthenia gravis, aspiration, bronchial secretion retention and aspiration were assessed as medically significant.   Details of laboratory data not reported.  It was not reported if the patient received any additional corrective treatment before death.  At the time of reporting, event outcome for pneumonia, gastrointestinal haemorrhage, shock haemorrhagic, hypertension, atrial fibrillation, Guillain-Barre syndrome and myasthenic syndrome or myasthenia gravis was not reported at the time of reporting. The muscular weakness, acute respiratory failure, aspiration and bronchial secretion retention were the events which were listed in death summery hence outcome of these events was considered as Fatal.  At the time of reporting, date of death was not reported.   It was unknown if an autopsy was done also the cause of death was clearly reported.  There will be no information available on the batch number for this case.; Sender's Comments: This case involved a 84 year old male patient who presented with muscular weakness, acute respiratory failure, aspiration, bronchial secretion retention, pneumonia, gastrointestinal haemorrhage, hypertension, atrial fibrillation, Guillain-Barre syndrome and myasthenic syndrome or myasthenia gravis after the administration of FLUBLOK QIV. Although time of onset is compatible for muscular weakness and acute respiratory failure, concurrently present Lambert Eaton Syndrome and gastrointestinal hemorrhage may indicate complications of existing comorbidities offering potential alternative etiology. At the time of reporting patient had ongoing coronary artery disease. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 48 or 49 hours after getting the first vaccination shot is when all the adverse conditions began to occur.    I was taking extra strength Tylenol every 3 1/2 hours which would barely minimize any of the problems !!!!     I usually have a body temp of 96.7, but started with a continuous 99.6 to 99.9 fever (six days) and had horrible chills for 4 days.   In addition, I suffered from severe headaches, nose bleeds, nausea, stomach discomfort, total lack of appetite,  EXTREME joint pain from head to toes, EXTREME sensitivity and pain on all skin surfaces (couldn't stand the weight of covers on me and could feel the texture of clothings' materials),  never before sciatica pain down right leg, totally flared up the pain in feet (from previous reaction to Levaquin) to a point of not being able to walk on feet, pain in and around both arm pits,    My blood pressure went totally out of control and kept going up to 190s.     All these "over the top" adverse conditions continued for 6 days --- then on day 7 and 8 they began to let up and I experienced what I would call more like regular "flu like symptoms"  It was as if any flaw or tolerable pre-existing discomforts I have had anywhere in my body were extremely exaggerated .
LAB_DATA: Doctor's visit.   Increase in blood pressure medication.
OTHER_MEDS: Xarelto, Irbesartan, Verapamil ER, Metoprolol Tartrate, Vit D, multivitamin,
HISTORY: Cardio, seasonal allergies, damage to ligaments/tendons in feet from Levaquin, some degeneration of back discs.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, Sulfa, Levaquin, food colorings; plus SUPER sensitive to ginger, many other antibiotics, various make up/lotions/hair products, and various spices

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 57y/o female presents with mild throat tightness ~15min after receiving Pfizer vaccine into the left arm. She states that it feels as though something small got stuck in her throat and is causing mild discomfort. She reports associated injection site pain, body cramps, and headache. She denies itching, difficulty breathing, shortness of breath, chest pain, palpitations, blurry vision, presyncope, difficulty swallowing water, or lip/tongue swelling. She reports no change in symptoms after 40min. post-injection.   Physical Exam:  Heart Rate 66bpm, Blood Pressure 115/74, Repeat Blood Pressure at 40min post-injection 120/80 Cardiac: regular rate and rhythm Lungs: unlabored breathing, clear to auscultation bilaterally  Skin: no injection site erythema or swelling. No rash.  No lip/tongue swelling or narrowing of oropharynx.   Plan:  Patient reports that her symptoms have improved at 1hr post-injection and would like to leave. I advised her that she should wait until all of her symptoms have resolved as throat tightness is a concerning adverse reaction. I provided her with options including contacting EMS right now to take her for observation at the hospital, however, the patient declined and said she would not go in the ambulance.  She insisted that she wanted to go home and that her husband was driving and would take her to the emergency room if her symptoms worsen. Patient was well-appearing when she left the vaccination site.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received vaccine in the AM of 3/16/21.  Patient was in his usual state of health when he went to bed the evening of 3/16/21.  He ate dinner normally and his PD was started as usual.  There were no overnight complications with his PD and he got up shortly before 8 AM.  Mom reports the dialysate from his bag was clear and normal and none of his dwell was retained.  She heard a loud thud from the bathroom around 8 AM and the patient was found by his mother having generalized convulsions (bilateral upper and lower extremities) and he appeared to be foaming at the mouth.  He did not respond to her and she called 911. The seizure stopped by the time EMS arrived and his initial GCS was 12, and 15 by the time they started transport.  He had another seizure en route around 9:30 AM and was given 2.5 mg versed and required bagging. Patient was loaded with Keppra and now has been on maintenance Keppra. Patient has not suffered any additional seizures and is currently undergoing an extensive workup by inpatient neurology team. Vaccine adverse effect currently remains on the differential for inciting event leading to seizure however additional labs are pending to rule out other causes (eg. viruses causing PML).  Patient was also diagnosed with multifocal pneumonia and started on antibiotics at time of admission.
LAB_DATA: EEG on 3/18/21: It is suggestive of severe diffuse encephalopathy of nonspecific etiology. Bisynchronous rhythmic slow waves with a wide distribution (GRDAs), are usually associated with a diffuse encephalopathy. GRDAs occasionally occurs in the setting of  widespread structural damage involving subcortical and cortical gray matter to a great extend than white matter and in the  setting of circumscribed structural lesions involving mesial frontal, diencephalic or brain stem structures. Therefore  clinical and neuroimaging correlations are strongly recommended.   MRI brain without contrast on 3/20/21: Asymmetric scattered regions of predominantly right-sided subcortical signal abnormality of a posterior predominance. This is a somewhat nonspecific appearance which could be seen in the setting of posterior reversible encephalopathy syndrome/acute hypertensive encephalopathy, though could also be seen with other etiologies including infectious processes such as progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy or other encephalitides.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up around 3 am with a mild headache, soreness, and mild fever. Went back to sleep and woke up again around 7 am.  Had mild fever and soreness throughout the day, but all symptoms subsided by the end of the day. Slight soreness at the vaccination site persisted for an additional day before subsiding.

My arm became very sore about 20 minutes after the vaccination, and continued to become more sore and painful. I woke at about 3 am the morning after the vaccination with flu symptoms, very similar to a those in a 3-week illness from last March, 2020. Sinus pain and pressure, low fever, muscle aches, weakness. I was the same later that day, the and continued to have a low fever. By the next day those symptoms were gone, but I felt weak and very fatigued, chilled, and slept much of the day. The symptoms of extreme fatigue, feeling chilled, continued until late on Friday evening, the 19th. I am normally a very active person, but the fatigue was frightening, and not something I normally suffer from. From about 2pm on each day after being vaccinated, my energy plummeted, and the extreme fatigue set in and I slept all afternoon each day and then all night, each day feeling okay in the mornings, then boom, extreme fatigue beginning around 2 pm. I have only experience this kind of fatigue once when I had the flu many years ago, and also last March when my doc thought I had Covid, sent me to the emergency room to be tested, but at that time, they were only testing people who had just returned from China. I want to stress, I am rarely ill, I am very active, and to date am on no medications except vitamins. But last March I was very ill for three weeks then about three more weeks were needed for recovery.  My symptoms from this second vaccination have subsided, but with a small amount of fatigue remaining in the afternoons. So, I wonder, from the studies coming out, that I may have indeed had Covid last March, and my immune reaction to the second vaccine was extremely strong. And, possibly I only needed the first vaccination. I filed a Vaers report on my symptoms after the first vaccination, that were also strong, including Covid arm, but subsided about 5 days after that vaccination, a month earlier.
PRIOR_VAX: ill for about 4 days after annual flu shots
ALLERGIES: Allergies to gluten, milk products, and minor allergies to some nuts.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am a well-nourished (doctor-speak for chunky), 65-year old female in fairly good health.  My main issue is severe rheumatoid arthritis, for which I take Humira (abdulimumab) by injection every two weeks.  I?ve been taking this medication for years and it has managed my condition well.  March 5 I received my (Janssen) vaccine and suffered no side effects, not even swelling or discomfort at the injection site.  Piece of cake!  March 11 I took my regular injection of Humira.  Pain started in my ankles, wrists, elbows and knees, increasing through the evening.  I developed a sore throat, but there were no other signs of allergic reaction.  Pain increased, waking me through the night.  March 12 Discomfort has increased severely.  Can?t put weight on my right leg and the slightest movement of any part of my body causes searing pain, especially in right leg from mid-thigh to below the knee.  I can?t lift the leg on its own; have to move it using my hands.  Pain is a constant 10, and I?m crying like a baby.  My left foot shows gout-like symptoms with heat, swelling and pain at the base of the toes.  The entire foot is very tender to the touch.  Taking Norco every six hours and using a cane.  I?m not a wimp.  I spent 10 years in the military, have had two total knee replacements, a reconstructed ankle and fought breast cancer twice.    March 13 Pain has diminished, but is still localized in the ankles, knees, wrists and elbows.  Taking ibuprofen instead of Norco, drinking a lot of liquids and icing swollen foot.  The most intense discomfort evolved during the 24 hours following the Humira injection.  I?m not a clinician, but it seems that the Humira didn?t react well to the introduction of the vaccine.  It?s as if it was saying ?Sorry, this spot is already taken,? and decided to duke it out.  I?m a bit concerned about the next dose of Humira, but the vaccine has supposedly done its work within two weeks.
OTHER_MEDS: Humira .4ml/40 mg once every two weeks; alendronate sodium 35 mg once weekly.  Daily:  letrazole 2.5 mg;   sertraline 75 mg;  multivitamin;   vitamin D3;   81 mg aspirin;  probiotic.

tingling in her mouth and lips; lump in throat; dizziness; tunnel vision; shaking; headache; anaphylaxis; A spontaneous report was received from a physician concerning a 26-year-old female patient who received Moderna (mRNA-1273) vaccine and experienced Anaphylactic reaction, having tingling in patient's mouth and lips and a lump in their throat, very bad headache, dizziness, tunnel vision and shakiness.  The patient's medical history included: allergy to azithromycin and penicillin. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.    On 19 Feb 2021, approximately four minutes prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: 031L20A) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.    On 19 Feb 2021 at 14.09, the patient had tingling in their mouth and lips and a lump in their throat. The patient's heart rate noted was 130s. The patient also reported very bad headache dizziness and tunnel vision. The patient developed shakiness which was noted on exam. The reporter reported for an anaphylaxis reaction .  The patient's Blood pressure reported was 156/80. At 14.29, the patient's Blood pressure reported was 176/87.  Treatment information provided included EpiPen (0.3mg) given Intramuscularly to right thigh at 14.22 and supplemental O2 provided. The reporter stated ambulance was called, husband of the patient was called. Reports were given to ambulance services. The systolic BP upon transport was 168.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event(s) was Not applicable.  On 19 Feb 2021, the outcome of the events, having tingling in patient's mouth and lips and a lump in their throat, very bad headache, dizziness and tunnel vision were considered resolved and the outcome of the event, shakiness was considered not resolved.  On an unknown date, the outcome of the event, Anaphylactic reaction was considered unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the se events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
CUR_ILL: Allergy to antibiotic (Allergic to azithromycin(vomiting)); Penicillin allergy (Allergic to penicillin (Rash))

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Unable to speak; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse concerning an eighty-year-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced the event unable to speak (aphasia).  The patient's ongoing medical conditions included congestive heart failure (CHF), hypertension, hyperlipidemia, diverticulitis, asthma, osteoarthritis, allergy to prednisone and allergy to tape.   Relevant concomitant medications included acetaminophen, amlodipine, cetirizine, colace with senna, fish oil, furosemide, gabapentin, glucosamine, meloxicam, hydrocodone/acetaminophen, metaxalone, montelukast, multivitamin, occuvite, omeprazole, sertraline and trazodone.  On 06-Feb-2021, approximately two days prior to the onset of events, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch# 016M20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 07-Feb-2021, the patient stated they were fine.  On 08-Feb-2021, the patient was found by their daughter in the evening unable to speak.  The patient was brought to the ED (emergency department) where they were later admitted for one day. The patient underwent a CT(computerized tomogram) scan on 08-FEB-2021 which showed no evidence of bleed  On 09-FEB-2021, the patient had an MRA (magnetic resonance angiogram) done which showed no aneurysm, dissection or stenosis. A 71-year-old female patient received first dose of BNT162B2 (Pfizer-Biontech Covid-19 Vaccine), lot no. EL9269, via an unspecified route of administration on 13Feb2021 at a single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. Medical history was not reported. There were no concomitant medications. The physician asked if there were any reports of paresthesia around the gums and/or tingling in the hands and fingers. The patient received the first dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. About 1 week after receiving the vaccine (20Feb2021), she experienced symptom complex, consistent with a mild peripheral neuropathy/sensory peripheral neuropathy around her gums and lips on her left side, as well as tingling on 4 of the 5 fingers of her left hand, She was admitted and a full workup for central disorders and vascular disorders was negative (Feb2021). But her symptoms were continuing intermittently. She had numbness of the gums. A portion of the trigeminal nerve on the left side seemed to have been impacted. Also, peri-orally on the left side.  The physician asked if this symptom complex has been reported and if there were reports of these mild sensory peripheral neuropathies coming from the vaccine. The physician stated that any info on dental paresthesia or any reports of other incidents of sensory paresthesia would be very helpful. The patient also called about the COVID 19 vaccine. On 13Feb, she got the vaccine in and then one week later on the following Saturday, the date would have been 20Feb, she started having a sensation of tingling and paralysis in her lips and gums all the way down to her finger tips on the side of the injection which was the left side and that has continued. She went to see the doctor the following Monday 22Feb and not knowing what it was, she sent her to the ER she was kept overnight, she was discharged 23Feb but her symptoms persisted even through today. These sensations were happening on average 3 times per day, sometimes many more anywhere from 3 minutes to 1 hour 45 minutes then it goes away. She did not go to her primary care. She confirmed her first dose was given 13Feb and the tingling and paralysis started the 20Feb it was still ongoing at this time. It has persisted but she can't tell whether it was getting better or not because sometimes it will last 3 minutes sometimes it will last 1 hour and 45 minutes. It started to effect other parts of her so she thinks it might be getting a little bit worse. It was starting to effect other parts of her body the progression goes, it started at the tip of her tongue and gums and then shortly within 30 seconds or less than a minute it spread to her upper and lower lip only on the left side and that was how it was on her gums as well it was only on the left side then she had the tingling in her finger tips on the left hand. She specified that she experienced these sensations on the tip of her tongue, left gums, lower left lip, and into the fingers on the left hand. She would like to know if these symptoms have been reported in association with the vaccine and if so, how long she can expect them to last. She stated that yesterday, a physician called in on her behalf for more information and said he received literature from 29Jan regarding reports that included information about dental paresthesia after the vaccine. She was planning not to get the second vaccine. She was not taking medications, she was in good health she did go and was admitted in the ER, they did a work up. Her blood pressure had sky rocketed on Feb2021 and since she mentioned sensation they ruled out a stroke. On Feb2021, they did blood work, MRI and CT scan and everything was they did not find anything linking to a stroke. She spent the night in observation. She was in the ER, they did put her in the main hospital but it was for observation from the emergency room. She went in on the 22Feb and was discharged home on 23Feb. She asked where this goes from here, these symptoms were concerning to her. She did not find any incidences at least in general of reporting this, asked if there were these kinds of things being reported, she didn't know how long it was going to last or if it will get worse. The outcome of blood pressure had sky rocketed was unknown while outcome of other events was not recovered.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Roughly a week following vaccination he cut his hand and was unable to stop the bleeding. 2 days later he developed mucosal lesions inside his mouth which began to bleed without resolution. He also cut himself shaving with prolonged bleeding. Following this event his rehabilitation center performed a CBC and he was found to be profoundly thrombocytopenic with platelets of 7. He presented to hospital where he was transfused with platelets which did not resolve his thrombocytopenia. He was transfused 2 more units with immediate CBC followup which did not improve his platelets; this was very suggestive of a consumptive process. Hematology was consulted and per their recommendations steroids were started. After initiation of systemic IV medrol platelet count began to rise. Per our hematology team, most likely culprit is the COVID vaccine. Patient had no medication changes, had been stable in his chronic conditions, and had never had any autoimmune or thrombocytopenic event before this time.
LAB_DATA: Various CBCs showing initially platelets of 8 (3/18/2021) resolving to 41 after day 4 of IV steroids (3/22/2021)

Patient presented to COVID-19 vaccination clinic for Moderna dose 1. When checking in at registration, patient was asked if this was for his first or second dose and patient stated he was here for the second dose.  When checked in at vaccination station, the first nurse asked patient screening questions.  When asked if he had received any immunizations within the past two weeks, patient stated no. When documenting the vaccine, the nurse received a EMR alert for vaccine duplication. When reviewing the chart further, nurse did not see additional vaccines administered that would contraindicate dose and asked another nurse to confirm. The second nurse also did not see vaccine contraindications in the chart. During this time a third nurse screened the patient again and the patient denied having received any vaccinations in the past two weeks. Patient was vaccinated with Moderna dose #1.  In the meantime, the clinic site manager reviewed the outside records in the patients chart, it was noted that the patient received the J&J COVID-19 vaccine on 3/11. The patient was asked if he had received the vaccine and he said yes and that he had looked at the research and he wanted to get the Moderna vaccine as that what was recommended.  Patient has now received one dose of J&J vaccine on 3/11 and one dose of Moderna vaccine 11 days later on 3/22. No adverse reactions identified during clinic observation period. SYMPTOM_TEXT: On March 16th at roughly 1:30pm, the patient received his first dose of the COVID19 Moderna vaccine. Afterward, the patient experienced no adverse side effects. About 48 hours later, however, at 2pm on March 18th, the patient's spouse attempted to wake him from a nap. The patient seemed much groggier than normal and his expression appeared vacant. When pressed by his spouse, the patient could not say who he was, or who his wife was. He agreed to travel with his wife to the hospital. At the hospital, a healthcare professional asked the patient who he was. He answered with his correct name. He also correctly identified his spouse by name. But when asked where he was, the patient gave a long and incoherent response. After this initial screening, doctors at the hospital evaluated the patient for a stroke. They ruled this out as a possibility. Next, they suspected the patient's MS lesions may have contributed to his "cognitive event." However, after comparing his 2018 scan to a current scan, they determined this was unlikely the cause. After about 24 hours at the hospital, a neurologist hypothesized that the patient had experienced a seizure. Another doctor at the facility concurred with this assessment. By late Friday (more than 24 hours after the episode), the patient had regained most of their cognitive functioning, though he still experienced mild confusion around the week's events (even preceding the "cognitive event"). Prior to now, the patient has never had a seizure before.

postherpetic neuralgia; hearing loss; balance problems; multiple outbreaks of herpes zoster; Information has been received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation referring to a patient (pt) of unknown age and gender. Information about concurrent condition, medical history and concomitant medication was not reported. On an unknown date, the pt was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (strength, dose, lot#, expiration date and route unknown) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). After receiving the vaccine, the pt suffered multiple outbreaks of herpes zoster, postherpetic neuralgia, hearing loss and balance problems. As a result of these symptoms, the pt was seen and treated by medical providers and was still under their care. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the product. The pt also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of the pt's condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of the vaccine, the pt suffered serious, progressive, permanent and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events was not recovered. The causality assessment was considered as related by the lawyer.  Upon internal review, hearing loss was determined to be medically significant. The lawyer considered all the events to be disabling.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 12 hours post-vaccine my heart rate was 115-125 beats per minute for over 5 hours and it was uncontrollable. No sleep, vomiting. The rapid heart rate that was so strong and persistent that it caused my brain to think my body was going to die. I had uncontrollable, racing and intrusive thoughts about the fact that I was about to die and I became incredibly scared and paranoid. I had minor "sleep" paralysis at times where I couldn't move my limbs and they felt incredibly heavy when I attempted to move (sleep in quotation marks because I did not sleep that night).   The intrusive, racing thoughts were spiraling incredibly rapidly - roughly 3 thoughts per second for the entire 5 or so hours that my heart rate was uncontrollable. When attempting to re-direct my thoughts, I was unsuccessful. Scenes/moments from my life flashed before my eyes in shuffle mode (i.e., memories from different parts of my life in no particular order) and at some points there were dark figures/shadows in my imagination that made it seem like I was about to die. My extremities became icy cold as if blood was drained from the areas during this time. I couldn't decide if I would be found dead in my bed or if I should go to the ER. I ultimately stayed home and tried to overcome the side effects (which I did).  Once my heart rate normalized the following morning, the racing and spiraling thoughts lessened, though there is an underlying fear of having these uncontrollable, intrusive, and racing thoughts return at any time.

I was walking out of my apartment building to my car inside the garage on Friday at 6:00 pm. As I was walking, my arms & legs began to feel heavy. By the time I reached the garage I was feeling extremely fatigued. I got inside of my car and thought to myself that I've never felt this tired in all of my life. I then felt very cold and decided it was best to go back upstairs.  When I into my apartment unit - my cats greeted me as if I was gone for an extremely long time - and I noticed the sun coming in through my windows when the sun should have been on the other side of the building at 6:00 pm. Both the cats & the sunshine told me something was very wrong. I looked at the clock - it said 8:08. I put on the tv and discovered it was 8:08 A.M. on Saturday morning. I had fallen asleep (or passed out) in my car from 6pm Friday evening until 8am Saturday morning.  I have no sleeping disorders & do not require naps during the day. Today I still feel fatigued, but only slightly.  From the time I entered my car at 6pm Friday - until the time I exited my car at 8am Saturday - it felt as though only moments had passed. I had no idea I had fallen asleep or passed out.

seizure / hospitalized for having seizure; trouble talking; biting her lips and as a result was bleeding all over.; feel sluggish.; Fatigue; runny nose; sneezing; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 75-year old, female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced was Seizure, trouble talking, runny nose, sneezing, biting her lips and as a result was bleeding all over, Very upset / frustration, feel sluggish, and fatigue.  The patient's medical history was not provided by the reporter. Current history includes stroke. Concomitant medications were carvedilol 12.5 bid, losartan 100mg, rovastatin 20mg, ezetimibe 10mg, levothyroxine 75 mcg, aspirin 81mg  On 28-Jan-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 026L20A) intramuscularly in the unknown location for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 25-Feb-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 014M20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 26-Feb-2021, the patient experienced seizure which occurred less than 24 hours after receiving the 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine.  At approximately 10:00 am, the patient wasn't able to formulate a sentence, similar to when she had a stroke. Husband drove her to the ER and she had a seizure in the car. CT Scan showed no stroke, showed a seizure. Patient was admitted, kept overnight, intubated and administered anti-seizure medicine. On 27-Feb-2021, the patient was discharged and developed flu-like symptoms (runny nose, sneezing, fatigue). Flu-like symptoms have cleared. The reporter feels the seizures are related to the prior stroke history.   On 10-Mar-2021, a follow-up was received. Patient feel huge disappointment and frustration on reporting serious adverse reaction. New information about the event include that on 26-Feb-2021, her husband noticed she was biting her lips and as a result was bleeding all over. Patient stated she has never had history of seizure but after this incident neurologists put her on high dose anti-seizure medications twice daily. These medications make her feel sluggish. I got my vaccine on 3/19 at 10am. My 6:30 pm on 3/19 my face got dark red, almost purple and started to swell. I went to and urgent care where they gave me a 50 mg shot of Benadryl. AFter about 20 minutes the reaction was getting better so they released me to go home. They told me to continue taking the Benadryl every 4-6 hours for the next 2-3 days. I did as directed for through the night and the next day. Around 6:30 pm on 3/20 I started feeling very tired, shaky, and dazed. My about 9:00 that evening I began to feel swelling in  my throat/tongue. I then went to the emergency room and where they gave me another 50 mg shot of Benadryl and a 6 mg shot of Decadron. They monitored me for a couple hours and the swelling in my mouth had gone down and the rash that had also reappeared had gone down. They sent me home with a prescription for Prednisone 10mg 4 pills a day for 4 days and told me to continue the Benadryl. I took the Prednisone and Benadryl for all day 3/21 and was feeling better. When I woke up on 3/22, my chest and arms had a rash on them. I took a Benadryl around 7:30 and Prednisone around 8:30. I went to work and around 10:30 my face started getting red and swelling again. I contacted my dermatologist who did skin patch testing and got an appoint for 3/22 at 1:45. She extended the Prednisone out to 12 days and told me to switch to Zytrec during the day and I will follow up on three weeks.
OTHER_MEDS: Metformin, Beyaz, HCTZ, Propanalol, Zytrec, Singulair, Omeperazole, Spironolactone, Citalopram

Patient was transported to hospital via ambulance at 06:45 pm on 3/11/21. Unknown tests performed.  Patient reports receiving IVs and medications for blood pressure while in ER. patient received Quadracel rather than intended Daptacel; with no reported AE; Initial information was received on 05-Oct-2020 regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case from nurse.  This case involves a nine-month-old patient (gender unknown) who received DIPHTHERIA-15/TETANUS/5 HYBRID AC PERTUSSIS/IPV (MRC5) VACCINE [QUADRACEL] (lot C5772AA, expiry date not reported) via an intramuscular route in the left thigh for prophylactic vaccination on 02-Mar-2021 instead of DIPHTHERIA-15/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE [DAPTACEL] (wrong product administered).  Medical history, concomitant therapy, medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided. Concomitant medications included HIB VACCINE and PNEUMOCOCCAL VACCINE CONJ 13V (CRM197) (PREVNAR 13).  It was reported that, the patient receiving her six-month series late. The office was out of Pentacel, so they administered HIB-PRPT with Quadracel vaccine in error (intended Daptacel) and Prevnar-13. Nurse reports that they typically use Pentacel for children's 6-month vaccines.  This was a case of actual medication error due to wrong vaccine administered (latency same day).  At the time of report, no adverse event was reported.  This suspected adverse reaction report is submitted and classified as a medication error solely and exclusively to ensure the marketing authorization holders compliance with the requirements. The classification as a medical error is in no way intended, nor should it be interpreted or construed as an allegation or claim made by the marketing authorization holder that any third party has contributed to or is to be held liable for the occurrence of this medication error.

Received shot ~12:15pm on March 21st. Only symptom throughout the day was sore arm, but tolerable. Around 10:30 PM, I was in bed and noticed that I feel "agitated" and restless. Looked at my FitBit and noticed that my heartrate was unusually high and climbing. My normal resting heartrate is 60-70 bpm. Last night from 10 PM and onward, it rose from 75 pm up to 130  bpm while I was laying down in bed. Soreness in my arm became much worse and more uncomfortable. I focused on breathing slowly and deeply to try to relax myself but did not have any effect. Throughout the night I could feel my heart racing, fluttering and palpitating. Sometimes I could feel "pinching" like sensations too. Every time I was able to fall asleep, I was quickly jolted awake by those fluttering and racing sensations in my chest. I got up ~2 hours later to get a drink of water and had a low-grade panic attack (lost sense of hearing), felt very weak and light-headed, started sweating profusely. Those symptoms let up a bit around 4AM and I was able to sleep lightly. I continued to feel "agitated" and restless all morning until about noon today, a full 24 hours after the shot, 12 hours after symptoms started. My resting heart rate finally started to return to normal at about that time as well. Felt fine and pretty normal by about 1:30ish PM today.
OTHER_MEDS: Zenpep 25s (pancreatic enzymes) Advair Trikafta  Lexapro Adderall Collagen Melatonin

On  Sunday 2/14, pt notes that she experienced chills and "just felt out of sorts." On 3/15 at 1:30pm, she was scheduled for a wellness exam with her primary care provider. She notes that when staff took her vital, they were concerned because she seemed short of breath. Pt notes that she is overweight and does have dypsnea on exertion at times, but staff were concerned because she had been at rest for some time and they considered the shortness of breath unusual. Pt reports that her blood pressure was normal and her O2 sats were running 97-98% on room air. However, her pulse was 150. An EKG was done and the physician voiced concern over how long her pulse had been elevated. She was transferred to the ED,  where per her report another EKG showed that she was in  atrial flutter. Pt reports that she was treated with IV Cardizem and given and IV bolus of magnesium.  At approximately 4:30pm, a CT with contrast was completed to rule out blood clot or PE. A third EKG done in the ED revealed that she had returned to normal sinus rhythm. She was discharged home at 6:30pm.  Pt reports that she was seen for follow up on 3/20. At that time, her physician ordered repeat labs - CMP, potassium, magnesium, and thyroid - all of which were normal per her report. He changed her medication from baby aspirin 81 mg to Zarelto 20 mg, noting that she is at high risk for stroke. Cardiology has been alerted and she has an ECHO scheduled . Since her discharge from the ED, pt has been monitoring her pulse daily and it have ranged from 66-72 bpm/

SYMPTOM_TEXT: got her first Moderna COVID19 vaccination on Wednesday 03/10/2021. She had no immediate problems with the shot such as arm pain or any other concerns, but by the next day 03/11/2021 she woke feeling very exhausted. They were having tests, and she is one of the main people in charge of this, so she just wrote it off as a reaction to stress. However as the day went on she was feeling worse including low-grade chronic headache, nausea, intermittent palpitations and waves of dizziness. She even had a little anxiety attack, thus she went home Thursday afternoon. She forced herself to go back to school the next day, knowing that if she could get through that day, she'd have a whole week off for spring break. Unfortunately, despite decreased stress, she continued to feel poorly. She has a feeling of profound fatigue, constant headache at the base of the skull that Tylenol really doesn't touch, nausea, stomach rumbling, intermittent dizziness, and intermittent palpitations.  Not surprisingly, her anxiety has increased, so she started sertraline 25 mg one half tab on Tuesday 03/16/2021, and on Saturday 03/20/2021 she increased it to a full tab. Now taking PharmaGABA at night to keep the anxiety and heart racing down.
OTHER_MEDS: Jolessa Tylenol Vitamin D Omega-3 Fatty Acids Melatonin

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Call received from patient who was advised to call to report a reaction to the COVID-19 vaccine. Patients history includes contracting COVID back in June of 2020 for which she spent 2 days in the hospital.  In November of 2020, she reports she ended up in the hospital for another 2 days and was diagnosed with post-COVID POTS.  She then went to medical facility and underwent 6 treatments of hyperbaric oxygen in February of 2021. Patient states that after these treatments, she felt great.  She has reportedly been out of work since November, I believe, and was given the OK to return on 3/10/21.  She was also advised by her neurologist that she should take the COVID vaccine which she did on 3/15/21.  Two days later, on 3/17/21, she states that her POTS was "triggered" and she begain to experience dizziness, fainting, fatigue, headaches, nausea and vomiting and various GI issues. Currently, she states these symptoms are getting worse, instead of better, and she has been unable to work, missing last Thursday and Friday, and will be going home early today.  She asks if she should get her second COVID vaccine.  I advised that is something she needs to discuss with her primary care provider.

I had the second Covid (Pfizer) vaccine on February 22. The next day I had chills, fever, aches, nausea and was very weak. After about 30 hours I felt okay again.  However, a week and a half later, I noticed red bumps on the back of my neck. The next day, my neck and scalp had red, itchy blotches. Through the next five days, these spread down my body to my ankles until I was covered with the red, very itchy blotches. I did go to Urgent Care on the third day and I was given a 5-day prescription of Prednisone. It did not do much until the third day and then it relieved the itching somewhat for about 6 hours, but then it would start again. After the five days of Prednisone, I took Benedryl for three days until the itch and redness disappeared.  I checked the facility web site on types of rashes and my rash fits the description (and the photo) of a drug-related rash, but I have not changed or added any drugs for several years other than the Covid vaccine (I did some research online and found two other people who have had the same problems I have had after the second Covid vaccine. Both of them had the typical reaction of chills, fever, aches and dizziness for about a day after the second shot and then 1-2 weeks later, broke out in a rash. Both reported having the rash start at the neck or head and then spreading down the body throughout one to two weeks before disappearing. There were photos on the facility site of drug-related rashes and they were exactly like what I had.  Since the rash was almost certainly covid vaccine related, I am making this report, which my doctor recommended. I had no other changes in diet, medications, environment, etc. ? only the Pfizer vaccine was new to my body.
LAB_DATA: None, NP in Urgent Care prescribed a 5-day prescription of Prednisone
OTHER_MEDS: Hydrochlorathiazide, Zyrtek, Magnesium Citrate, Biotin, Glucosamine Condroitin

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My Mom the next day, Saturday 3/20/22 had short term memory loss for a couple of hours.  My parents drove to the grocery store on Saturday afternoon.  After a few hours at the grocery store, my Dad went outside to the car and waited for my Mom while she pays for their groceries.  After waiting an hour, my Mom still hasn't come out so my Dad called her.  She told my Dad that she has no idea where she is.  My Dad went back to check on her and she said that she has no memory of her putting items in the car or talking to their friends earlier.  My Dad took her home to get some rest.  After a couple of hours, my Mom is still experiencing short term memory of not knowing what happen earlier as she kept going back to the car to check on their groceries, she kept saying "its 6 pm? where has the time gone", and she kept saying am I going crazy I can't remember what happen.  My Dad and their friends verified these events happen while she has no idea.  We told her to  just get a good night of sleep that night.  The next morning, she was feeling better and coherent remembering what happen last night and during the day but she still can't remember what happen in the few hours they were at the grocery store.  Today 2 days later, March 22 she is back to normal.
