SYMPTOM_TEXT: Background: pharmacy received 49 vials of Pfizer COVID vaccine (Lot number EN6199) on 5 March 2021 and stored them in the pharmacy refrigerator.   The doses were labeled with an expiration date of 10 March 2021 at 0701.   Since starting the COVID-19 vaccine program, the pharmacy has always used the doses before they approached the expiration date.  This time, there were 16 vials of the Pfizer vaccine that had not been used and set to expire. The labeled expiration date and time were clearly present on the outside of the bag containing the doses.  On the morning of 10 March 2021, a pharmacist retrieved 1 vial at 0754 and 7 vials at 1138 from that allocation and provided them to nursing for the day?s administrations.  The pharmacy placed those doses in a new amber bag and did not label the bag with an expiration date and time.   The nursing team received the vials, diluted and drew up 20 doses that were administered to patients before 1230.    The charge nurse did not question the expiration date until after 20 patients had been vaccinated.  At that time she messaged the pharmacist to verify the expiration date.  The pharmacist indicated that the label did not state am or pm and misinterpreted the expiration time for the doses as 7:01 PM rather than 7:01 AM.  There was not a defined double check at the time of distribution from the pharmacy to nursing  The remaining 11 vials were quarantined.  The pharmacy manager contacted the manufacturer.  According to Pfizer it?s recommended to use the thawed vaccine within 120 hours, but can be used up to 144 hours.  The doses in question were administered before 125 hours after they were thawed.  The remaining expired vials will be wasted and appropriate notifications sent.  Assessment: Twenty patients received Pfizer COVID vaccine 5 hours passed the labeled expiration date and time.  While exceeding the manufacturer?s recommended beyond use dating, the doses were within the acceptable 144 hours post thaw period and still safe for patient administration.  There was misinterpretation of the labeled expiration time by the dispensing pharmacist, the container of COVID vaccine vials provided to nursing was not labeled with an expiration date or time, there was not a double check on hand off, the nursing team did not double check the expiration date/time before dilution or administration.  Recommendation:  When repackaging COVID Vaccine vials for distribution to vaccination centers, a label including the expiration date and time should be placed on the new container. SYMPTOM_TEXT: @ 3-5 min... arm started feeling a little sore, like a dead arm. That was the extent of things for a few hours.   @ 4 hours... randomly while doing absolutely nothing started getting short of breath + breathing through a tube feeling + drastically increased brain fog.   @ 11 hours... splitting headache + arm at the injection site painful to the touch + combination of pain/discomfort kept me awake all night despite my sleep Rx for insomnia.   @ 17-18 hours later... leg muscles were sore and achy and cramping if I stayed in any position for too long. Began to feel feverish yet had no temperature (yet). My saturation which frequently drops but always rebounds fairly quickly stayed at about 90% for over an hour.   @ about 20 hours... I began to get swollen lymph nodes and my temperature started climbing into the high 90?s (my ?normal? is around 97� so this made me feel like I was on fire). My SpO2 dropped to 84%... the lowest I?d measured it, even when hospitalized for a week back in December. Everything also felt heavy?every part of my body, anything I?d try to pick up... as of gravity had suddenly increased.   @ 22 hours... low grade fever of 100.2� while on Tylenol... so w/o it likely would have been higher.   @ 24 hours later... (330pm next day) it all really hit me... my saturation dropped to 79%. With otc cans of oxygen it only went up to 84% and kept dropping back to 80%. I was unbearably hot and uncomfortable and sore everywhere, but especially my neck and shoulders. I had zero appetite.   @ 26 hours... chills so bad I couldn?t get warm when wearing a fleece, under 3 blankets, and head covered.   @ 29 hours... so nauseous I couldn?t eat + my temperature (still with Tylenol in my system) peaked at 101�.   @ around hour 30... so unbearably hot had to shed all the layers I?d put on + over me. My temperature was just barley back under 100� at this point (Tylenol still in system).   @ 34 hours... Overnight arm pain + chills retuned to the point woke up from sleep Rx. I had to take more Tylenol due the pain. Got fully dressed with hoodie + fleece on all under my comforter in bed. Despite deep chills my forehead felt like it was literally on fire, but I couldn?t find the thermometer so who knows what my temperature was.   @ 42 hours... dizzy + disoriented + saturation 86% + injection site pain.   @ 48 hours... appetite still suppressed + injection site pain (though less than at worst)

Background: Hesperia pharmacy received 49 vials of Pfizer COVID vaccine (Lot number EN6199) on 5 March 2021 and stored them in the pharmacy refrigerator.   The doses were labeled with an expiration date of 10 March 2021 at 0701.   Since starting the COVID-19 vaccine program, the Hesperia MOB has always used the doses before they approached the expiration date.  This time, there were 16 vials of the Pfizer vaccine that had not been used and set to expire. The labeled expiration date and time were clearly present on the outside of the bag containing the doses.  On the morning of 10 March 2021, a pharmacist retrieved 1 vial at 0754 and 7 vials at 1138 from that allocation and provided them to nursing for the day?s administrations.  The pharmacy placed those doses in a new amber bag and did not label the bag with an expiration date and time.   The nursing team received the vials, diluted and drew up 20 doses that were administered to patients before 1230.    The charge nurse did not question the expiration date until after 20 patients had been vaccinated.  At that time she messaged the pharmacist to verify the expiration date.  The pharmacist indicated that the label did not state am or pm and misinterpreted the expiration time for the doses as 7:01 PM rather than 7:01 AM.  There was not a defined double check at the time of distribution from the pharmacy to nursing  The remaining 11 vials were quarantined.  The pharmacy manager contacted the manufacturer.  According to Pfizer it?s recommended to use the thawed vaccine within 120 hours, but can be used up to 144 hours.  The doses in question were administered before 125 hours after they were thawed.  The remaining expired vials will be wasted and appropriate notifications sent.  Assessment: Twenty patients received Pfizer COVID vaccine 5 hours passed the labeled expiration date and time.  While exceeding the manufacturer?s recommended beyond use dating, the doses were within the acceptable 144 hours post thaw period and still safe for patient administration.  There was misinterpretation of the labeled expiration time by the dispensing pharmacist, the container of COVID vaccine vials provided to nursing was not labeled with an expiration date or time, there was not a double check on hand off, the nursing team did not double check the expiration date/time before dilution or administration.  Recommendation:  When repackaging COVID Vaccine vials for distribution to vaccination centers, a label including the expiration date and time should be placed on the new container.    When COVID vaccine is transferred from one location or department to the next, a double check of the product, quantity, integrity and expiration date and time may prevent a recurrence of this situation.

Background: the pharmacy received 49 vials of Pfizer COVID vaccine (Lot number EN6199) on 5 March 2021 and stored them in the pharmacy refrigerator.   The doses were labeled with an expiration date of 10 March 2021 at 0701.   Since starting the COVID-19 vaccine program, they always used the doses before they approached the expiration date.  This time, there were 16 vials of the Pfizer vaccine that had not been used and set to expire. The labeled expiration date and time were clearly present on the outside of the bag containing the doses.  On the morning of 10 March 2021, a pharmacist retrieved 1 vial at 0754 and 7 vials at 1138 from that allocation and provided them to nursing for the day?s administrations.  The pharmacy placed those doses in a new amber bag and did not label the bag with an expiration date and time.   The nursing team received the vials, diluted and drew up 20 doses that were administered to patients before 1230.    The charge nurse did not question the expiration date until after 20 patients had been vaccinated.  At that time she messaged the pharmacist to verify the expiration date.  The pharmacist indicated that the label did not state am or pm and misinterpreted the expiration time for the doses as 7:01 PM rather than 7:01 AM.  There was not a defined double check at the time of distribution from the pharmacy to nursing  The remaining 11 vials were quarantined.  The pharmacy manager contacted the manufacturer.  According to Pfizer it?s recommended to use the thawed vaccine within 120 hours, but can be used up to 144 hours.  The doses in question were administered before 125 hours after they were thawed.  The remaining expired vials will be wasted and appropriate notifications sent.  Assessment: Twenty patients received Pfizer COVID vaccine 5 hours passed the labeled expiration date and time.  While exceeding the manufacturer?s recommended beyond use dating, the doses were within the acceptable 144 hours post thaw period and still safe for patient administration.  There was misinterpretation of the labeled expiration time by the dispensing pharmacist, the container of COVID vaccine vials provided to nursing was not labeled with an expiration date or time, there was not a double check on hand off, the nursing team did not double check the expiration date/time before dilution or administration.  Recommendation:  When repackaging COVID Vaccine vials for distribution to vaccination centers, a label including the expiration date and time should be placed on the new container.    When COVID vaccine is transferred from one location or department to the next, a double check of the product, quantity, integrity and expiration date and time may prevent a recurrence of this situation.

Background: (Name) Pharmacy received 49 vials of Pfizer COVID vaccine (Lot number EN6199) on 5 March 2021 and stored them in the pharmacy refrigerator.   The doses were labeled with an expiration date of 10 March 2021 at 0701.   Since starting the COVID-19 vaccine program, the  MOB has always used the doses before they approached the expiration date.  This time, there were 16 vials of the Pfizer vaccine that had not been used and set to expire. The labeled expiration date and time were clearly present on the outside of the bag containing the doses.  On the morning of 10 March 2021, a pharmacist retrieved 1 vial at 0754 and 7 vials at 1138 from that allocation and provided them to nursing for the day?s administrations.  The pharmacy placed those doses in a new amber bag and did not label the bag with an expiration date and time.   The nursing team received the vials, diluted and drew up 20 doses that were administered to patients before 1230.    The charge nurse did not question the expiration date until after 20 patients had been vaccinated.  At that time she messaged the pharmacist to verify the expiration date.  The pharmacist indicated that the label did not state am or pm and misinterpreted the expiration time for the doses as 7:01 PM rather than 7:01 AM.  There was not a defined double check at the time of distribution from the pharmacy to nursing  The remaining 11 vials were quarantined.  The pharmacy manager contacted the manufacturer.  According to Pfizer it?s recommended to use the thawed vaccine within 120 hours, but can be used up to 144 hours.  The doses in question were administered before 125 hours after they were thawed.  The remaining expired vials will be wasted and appropriate notifications sent.  Assessment: Twenty patients received Pfizer COVID vaccine 5 hours passed the labeled expiration date and time.  While exceeding the manufacturer?s recommended beyond use dating, the doses were within the acceptable 144 hours post thaw period and still safe for patient administration.  There was misinterpretation of the labeled expiration time by the dispensing pharmacist, the container of COVID vaccine vials provided to nursing was not labeled with an expiration date or time, there was not a double check on hand off, the nursing team did not double check the expiration date/time before dilution or administration.  Recommendation:  When repackaging COVID Vaccine vials for distribution to vaccination centers, a label including the expiration date and time should be placed on the new container.    When COVID vaccine is transferred from one location or department to the next, a double check of the product, quantity, integrity and expiration date and time may prevent a recurrence of this situation.

I then take 2 motrin and about 30 mins later i notice theres a tightness in my chest. i take 1 tums. I know that my body is exhausted from the pain and my mind is clouded but i really wanted to do all of the tasks that i was planning on doing this weekend. (Dream start) The dream i had is of me watching myself get thrown around by a ghost. The ghost possesses my body for a short time. I grab some kittens (cats are a comfort to me so im guessing that my subconscious trying to reel me back in) I then wake my sleeping wife and tell her theres a ghost and we need to leave. We walk outside and im in an old neighborhood that i grew up in, everything darkens and im in pitch black feeling my way around a room. I open my eyes and im in a hotel. The front desk staff will not let me take the kittens up to my room so i leave them. The soreness prevents me from going back to sleep and the tightness in my chest causing some anxiety. Once I calm myself down and convince myself that im not having a heart attack I take 2 motrin and some tums and the pain goes away from the day. These could be some withdrawals from not taking amitriptyline since 19 mar in the morning. This is still happening as I write this report. (23 March 2021)

Per clinic notes: "Brief summary covid vaccine 1/21 with side effect within 12 hr lasting 3 d By around 1/26-1/29 had cp w/ exertion and sob TST 2/2 w/  Minor ekg changes and min workload per pt (mod workload per note) nuc study pending. Though no desat on march test, he has freq intermittent coughing and he was tachycardic to 110 on exam this am."   Pt states symptoms worsening over past week. No symptoms at rest. With exertion has anterior chest tightness and dyspnea. No radiation of pain or migration. He can walk usual distances but much slower. Improved at rest. Cannot lay flat at night. At 1:00 p.m. on Sunday the lymphnodes on the left side of the neck began hurting again (excruciating pain) and I again took 800 mg of ibuprofen to relieve the pain. After 40 min (2:10 p.m.) it felt better and I had a few potato chips left over from my lunch.  The numbness started again about 10 min later and lasted about 20 min. During the 15 minute observation period after injection, patient returned to the check-in desk complaining of dizziness. He was brought immediately to exam room where he became pale, diaphoretic, and stated he "felt like he was in a dream." Seated BP was 74/palp. He was placed in supine position on exam table, cool compresses placed on forehead and back of neck. He complained of some nausea, which quickly improved. He never lost consciousness. His color and alertness improved steadily over the next 10 minutes. Repeat BP (lying) was 100/50. After a few minutes he sat up on exam table, dangling legs. BP remained stable at 110/60, HR 84. He continued to improve and stated that he felt better, drank some water and ate some goldfish crackers. Reported that he just remembered he had not eaten since lunch. After another 5-10 minutes he was alert, oriented, able to walk unassisted. Final BP 114/70, HR 80. His wife remained with him and confirmed she could drive him home. Discussed that although I feel confident this was a vasovagal near-syncope, if symptoms recur or worsen, he should go to ER for evaluation. Understanding verbalized.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 10 minutes of receiving injection in right arm I felt a BOOM flush all over my body like I just had an IV Contrast. I was worked up for cardiac, lung, chemistry.  My troponin-HS was slightly elevated and a cardiologist was called.  He did an echo on my heart, liver and right kidney -- normal.  Chest X-ray was normal.  A second 12 lead EKG was done, normal sinus.  Hematology, Chemistry was normal.  Was in the ED from 11:30 to 4:00 p.m.  Advised by ED Doctor, and Cardiologist, that it seems the stress of the anaphylaxis reaction stressed the heart which caused the spill of troponin.  Advised to see my cardiologist and get a stress test.  I have already informed my Primary Care Doctor and he has prescribed me an EPI-PEN to carry.  I have no history of allergic reactions/anaphylaxis reactions to vaccines.  I am up to date with all other vaccines and just had my yearly flu shot in November 2020.  This was my first allergic reaction/anaphylaxis reaction to a vaccine.
LAB_DATA: Medical tests and laboratory results were taken on March 19, 2021 in the Emergency Department as soon as I was transported from the vaccination site to the ED.  Chest X-ray done.  One 12 lead EKG done.  One 12 lead EKG done in the ED .  Hematology done -- normal. SYMPTOM_TEXT: No pain or adverse event for the first 4 hours after vaccination. Starting at 2pm, which was 4 hours after my vaccine, , my chest began to tighten. It was not severe; I took a normal walk and was just mildly uncomfortable. It escalated hourly for about 10- 12 hours. At 8pm, the pain, pressure, and tightness around the chest went from mild to moderate, from a pain level of 2 to about 3 or 4. The sensation was one of a stack of books on my chest. There was pressure and mild pain (again, not severe), about 8-10 inches horizontally across my chest, from about the bottom of my sternum to the collarbone. I also felt some pressure in my lower throat, perhaps the bottom third of my neck. I did not have any shortness or breath, swelling, or difficulty swallowing. At about 9 pm, I became itchy on my neck, ankles, and flank. I developed some red spots, which were not large enough to be hives, They mostly became red from my itching, though they were more moderately itchy than seriously itchy. I have had hives before, and they did not appear to be hives, more just isolated red spots. Once I became itchy, I went to the ER. They worked me up for cardiac issues and a blot clot, but all tests were negative. I did not take any medication other than my standard Oxcarbazepine 8pm dose of 300 mg. The itchiness went away at about 11pm (two hours after onset), and the chest pain did not worsen. The following morning, it was significantly better, and about 36 hours after I first received the vaccine, it was gone entirely.
LAB_DATA: EKG - normal. Blood work - normal, though low sodium and chloride (which is a prior issue secondary to my Oxcarbazepine). Chest X ray - normal.
OTHER_MEDS: 750 mg Oxcarbazepine; 10mg Melatonin; monthly Aimovig; daily multivitamin; Ubrelvy 100mg; 4mg Granisetron occasionally; Yazmin birth control

In the past, I have had a very mild  and intermittent case of tinnitus. More than a week later, the tinnitus is almost debilitating --  CONSTANT and never getting any lower.    A "whooshing" sound that just won't stop.  It's maddening.    I've never had tinnitus this bad in my life and there is no reason for it to have gotten worse besides the vaccine.    It is high-pitched, and constant, and this is two weeks after receiving my dose.     It's only getting worse -- there has been no hint of quieting down.   I am very upset over this and it's obvious that my tinnitus got severe directly after I got the first Pfizer vaccine.   I've been living at home alone for the last year so it's certainly not due to loud music or anything like that.

Narrative:  Pt received his COVID vaccine at 1208. Pt stayed in the COVID vaccine waiting room for 15 minutes for observation per protocol. After leaving the clinic, patient came back around 1230 because he stated: "I am feeling stoned and loopy." Had the patient sit down in the ante room of the Covid vaccine clinic. 1234: While sitting, CNA noticed that pt had a blank stare, unresponsive, and started to lean towards his R side. 1235: clinic nurses and 911 were called. Patient's eyes rolled back and is eased the patient out of the chair onto the floor. Cleared the area around of anything hard or sharp. Pillow placed underneath patient's head. VS taken as follows: 130/75 HR 119 bpm, O2 Sat 99%. While on the floor, pt remained unresponsive to verbal or any noxious stimuli. 1238: Epipen administered on RUE. Pt woke and sat up asking what happened to him. Pt reports: "I forgot to tell you guys that I have history of seizures." Placed pt on O2 at 2lpm via nasal cannula. VS as follows: 130/75 hr 122 BPM, O2 Sat 99%. 1240: Pt had grand mal seizures again for 2 minutes. Placed pt on his L side. Dr. arrived. Pt is monitored with pulse oximetry. HR 119 bpm, O2 sat 99%. 1243: Pt woke up from his seizure and asked what happened. He stood up for about 10 seconds and pt suddenly lost his balance and knelt. 1245: EMS arrived, handoff given. Pt is transported to Medical Center.

Abdominal Pain, Dyspnea, Throat Irritation Narrative: 30 yo F with PMH multiple allergies, chronic pain syndrome, cervical and lumbar radiculopathy, and chronic plantar fasciitis, presenting with c/f anaphylaxis after receiving COVID-19 (Pfizer) vaccine. Had scheduled COVID-19 vaccine appointment at a medical center. Shortly after (about 1 minute) of administration she noted some GI upset initially and some dizziness on standing Then developed lip and finger tingling, some throat discomfort and tightness and SOB where she felt that she was not able to get any air out. Was instructed to  come to the ED for further eval. Has an epi-pen at home but did not administer. She said this felt very similar to prior allergic reactions she has had in the past. In the ED, was tachycardic to the 120s, vitals otherwise wnl. Labs notable for Cr 1.3 (baseline 0.8), hypokalemia to 3.0, d-dimer and trop neg. Given solumedrol 125mg IV, Benadryl 50mg IV and 0.5mg Ativan and symptoms significantly improved. Epi ordered but not given. Her symptoms improved after medication admin. Transferred to the floor for further eval. She has an extensive allergy history to azithromycin, morphine, peanuts, red dye, shellfish/seafood, oranges. She saw an allergist as a child but has not for some time. She has had similar reactions to this episode with exposures and usually take Benadryl/famotidine with resolution. Also has history of allergic rhinitis and chronic sinus issues. Patient's symptoms improved with overnight evaluation, although noted 2 episodes of emesis and EKG with sinus tachycardia. Patient stable with planned discharge with outpatient evaluation of sinus tachy. Per medical team this development is not likely related to acute event due to persistence.

54 y/o M presents today for a hospital F/U. He has not seen me for a routine visit since 08/2019. Pt presented to ER on 03/12/2021 with c/o elevated BP and exertional CP. He was noted to have an elevated troponin and transferred to medical center. Pt underwent Exercise stress test which did not show any signs of ischemia. He was discharged on 03/16/2021. Pt has f/u appt with his cardiologist, Dr. on 03/22/2021. Pt notes that he received his first Moderna COVID-19 vaccine dose on 03/11/2021. It was a few hours later that he began to feel the CP. As a result of the zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence, the pt suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. The appearance was of shingles; Rash along the medial aspect of my left breast / small amount on the lateral left breast; Rash has more of a scabbed appearance; This case was reported by a nurse and described the occurrence of shingles in a 53-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   On 8th February 2021, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix. On 13th February 2021, 5 days after receiving Shingrix and an unknown time after starting Valtrex, the patient experienced shingles and rash. In February 2021, the patient experienced scab. The patient was treated with valaciclovir hydrochloride (Valtrex). On an unknown date, the outcome of the shingles and rash were recovering/resolving and the outcome of the scab was unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the shingles, rash and scab to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The age at vaccination was not reported but it could be 52 or 53 years old. The patient received the first dose of the Shingrix vaccine on 8th February 2021 (Monday). On the following Saturday (13th February 2021), she noted a rash along the medial aspect of left breast with a small amount also on the lateral left breast. As the reporter was a nurse who worked with breast cancer patients and, hence had concerns of inflammatory breast cancer, she went to see a breast specialist on 16th February 2021 (Tuesday). The breast specialist reassured her that the appearance was not that of inflammatory breast cancer but was rather of shingles.  The patient was prescribed Valtrex which she was taking and was on day 6 on the reporting date. The rash was clearing up but was still present at the time of reporting and had more of a scabbed appearance at that time. The reporter was wondering if this had been noted in any other patients with Shingrix and was also inquiring if she should receive the second dose. The reporter consented to follow -up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Heart attack; Fatigue; Chest Pain; Cough; Fever; Muscle pain in chest area; Chills; A spontaneous report  was received from a 72 year-old female patient who was administered Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and developed heart attack (myocardial infarction), fever (pyrexia), cough, fatigue, muscle pain in chest area (myalgia), chills, and chest pain.  The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported.  On 25-JAN-2021, 26 hours prior to the onset of events, the patient received her second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot#: unknown) intramuscularly for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 26-JAN-2021, the patient reported they have developed chills, fever, and muscle pain in the chest area. The reporter specified that it wasn't chest pain.  The patient took acetaminophen for the pain. On 27-JAN-2021, the patient reported her fever subsided but she was still having a little cough and chest pain.  On 28-JAN-2021, the patient had chest pain again during a nap and decided to call 911 because she was about to pass out. The patient was taken to the ER (emergency room) where an EKG (electrocardiogram) was performed. A few moments after the EKG, the patient had a heart attack. The cardiologist suspected the patient may have had a heart attack two days earlier because her cardiac enzymes were too high to be a result of a recent heart attack. The patient was admitted to the hospital from 28-JAN-2021 until 01-FEB-2021. Catheterization and stent placement were performed. Treatment medications included acetaminophen, clopidogrel, metoprolol, low-dose aspirin, and atorvastatin. At the time of this report, the patient was still feeling fatigued but other than that, she was feeling better.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable.  The outcomes of the events, heart attack, cough, muscle pain in chest area, fever, chills, and chest pain, were resolved. The outcome of the event, fatigue, was not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: No adverse event (Medical history not provided)

Medical history included depression and anxiety, both from unknown dates and unknown if ongoing. The patient had no allergies to medication, food or other products, and did not have COVID-19 prior to vaccination. Concomitant medications included duloxetine from an unknown date for an unknown indication; ethinylestradiol, ferrous fumarate, norethisterone acetate (LARIN FE) from an unknown date for an unknown indication; ibuprofen from an unknown date for an unknown indication; and acetaminophen from an unknown date for an unknown indication. The patient had not received any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. The patient reported, it first started as a headache and extreme fatigue about two hours after the vaccine. She took two ibuprofen and felt better for a few hours, but the fatigue kept growing and then she started to get cold sweats and chills. The day after was the worse. She had fever, nausea, extreme muscle pain and fatigue, pain at the injection site, and congestion. She took acetaminophen through-out the day and couldn't eat much. The second day the fever and cold sweats went away but she still had intense nausea. It was the third day (as of 10Feb2021) and she felt better but still had fatigue and minor nausea. The events were reported as non-serious and did not require hospitalization. The clinical outcomes of headache, extreme fatigue, cold sweat, chills, fever, nausea, extreme muscle pain, congestion, couldn't eat much and pain at the injection site were reported as recovering. It was also reported that since vaccination, the patient had not been tested for COVID-19.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Headache/Sharp pain across the forehead; chills; body aches; tiredness; severe migraine; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse, the patient. A 39-year-old non-pregnant female patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE), via an unspecified route of administration in the left arm on 04Feb2021 at 14:45 (at the age of 39-years-old) as a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included depression-anxiety and birth control use; the patient had no known allergies. It was unknown if the patient was diagnosed with COVID-19 prior to the vaccination. Concomitant medications included vilazodone hydrochloride (VIIBRYD), drospirenone/ethinylestradiol betadex clathrate (YAZ) for birth control, clonazepam (KLONOPIN). The patient did not receive any other vaccinations within 4 weeks of the vaccine. On 04Feb2021 at 15:00 (also reported as within 3 minutes post vaccination), the patient experienced headache as a sharp pain across the forehead. On 04Feb2021 at 15:00, the patient also experienced chills, body aches and tiredness that lasted 24 hours. The headache remained 6 days post vaccination as a severe migraine, as of an unspecified date in Feb2021, for which no medications worked. The patient iced, applied heat to the area, dark room, no sound for 2 days and finally was relieved with acupuncture. This headache was like no headache the patient had ever had and she had come very close to an emergency room visit but realized it was from the vaccine. The events "Headache/Sharp pain across the forehead" and severe migraine resulted in a healthcare professional visit and the patient was treated for these events with acupuncture. Since the vaccination, the patient had not been tested for COVID-19. The clinical outcome of "Headache/Sharp pain across the forehead" and severe migraine was resolving; chills, body aches and tiredness were resolved on 05Feb2021 at 15:00.  Information on the lot/batch number has been requested.

This morning the pain has dropped to my right buttock and is radiating down my right leg; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer, the patient. A 71-year-old male patient received his first dose of BNT162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE; Lot Number: EL9264) via an unspecified route of administration in the left arm on 10Feb2021 (at the age of 71-years-old), for COVID-19 immunization. There was no medical history. The patient did not have any allergies to medications, food, or other products. The patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. There were no concomitant medications and no other vaccine was administered on the same date. Exactly one week after the injection, on 17Feb2021, the patient began having routine symptoms including weakness, tiredness, and chills. The unusual and unexpected symptom was a right flank pain that seemed to be over the right kidney. According to the patient, it seemed to be muscular, so he dismissed it. I have had a non-stop pressure headache since the second dose. I drink plenty of water. I take Tylenol / Ibuprofen daily. Nothing helps. Laying down makes it worse. It throbs in the roof of my mouth and my nose. It is nauseating. I feel like someone is squeezing my brain. My blood pressure, pulse, and oxygen are fine.   I did reach out to a neurologist about this. I was thought to have IIH over two years ago when I was 70 lbs heavier, but I have not had a symptom since losing weight. Opening pressures and scans show no evidence of it. The headaches I am having now are significantly worse than that was. It hurts down my neck as well.  The headaches began approximately 18 hours after the second dose. I was nauseated. I had chills. I had a temperature. My joints ached. My muscles ached. My body ached I was seen at the hospital twice for the seemingly common and expected side effects. I received IV medication for nausea and plenty of fluids. The headache, however, did not let up. 60ish hours after the second dose and all other symptoms ceased. The headache, however, remained. It persists. The headaches get so intense sometimes that my body feels like it needs to jerk, or twitch. I honestly cannot explain this sensation. I feel like I have to really focus to keep my body from moving impulsively.  It is bothersome, but I am concerned with how long it is lasting, especially with reports of strokes following the vaccination.
LAB_DATA: I had routine labs drawn for other reasons. Nothing was out of the norm. My vitals are okay.  I am awaiting a response from a neurologist.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Per provider on site: Patient received Covid 19 Pfizer vaccine approximately at 1:25 pm. She noted to feeling dizzy when she presented to my station about 15 minutes after her vaccine. She stated to having history of moderate asthma, carries albuterol with her. She denies drug allergy, but had lightheadedness with MMR vaccine in the past. I checked her pulse rate, 94 regular. 5 minutes later, she c/o feeling worse. She had inspiratory wheezing to auscultation, VS stable. BP 122/72, HR 103, pulse oximetry 99%. She had albuterol MDI inhaler with her, I asked her to self-administer 2 puffs. I administered 25 mg of diphenhydramine. She declined 50 mg because she gets very groggy to anti-histamine.  Approximately 3 minutes later, she noted to feeling like her throat is very dry and warm, almost difficult to swallow. She describes sensation like she is breathing thru a straw. Her vitals remain stable: BP 133/74, HR 128, pulse ox 98%. Throat without swelling, redness, no stridors noted, but she continues to have inspiratory wheezing. She declined to have Epi given.  I made decision to call paramedics given high risk for bronchospasm. Paramedics arrived approximately 7 minutes later. Vital signs remain stable. She continues to feel like she is "breathing through a straw." She is transported to ER

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1:45 driving home, started to notice weird feeling like I had an allergy shot. 2:30 I got home and breathing was aggravated. 2 puffs of inhaler, sat down and waited. I had a heart rate in 140s in triage, and a low BP around 90/60. My tongue continued to feel funny and started to get hard to talk. It felt heavy, but medical staff didn't think swollen. I was given a breathing treatment, Benadryl, Pepcid, IV fluids and monitored. 8:15 I was asked to walk a bit to make sure oxygen was staying up. My chest tightness was getting worse but since my oxygen stayed at 95 when walking, was discharged. I'm scheduling albuterol treatments every 4 hours around the clock and continue to take Pepcid and Benadryl in addition to my normal meds. 3/20 I developed uterine cramping, felt like I was having back labor as the result. LAB_DATA: Chest x ray - normal. EKG - HR in 140, but otherwise normal

High blood sugars for a week now.  My son is 16 year's old and was diagnosed with Type 1 Diabetes in November.  He is thin and active, and an otherwise healthy teen and runner.  He is in his "honeymoon phase" of diabetes and I think the vaccine may be killing off beta cells.  He went from having blood sugar levels in the 80's to 90's at 12 units of Lantus to now 120's to 130's and up to 160's immediately after the shot.  His mealtime insulin is also not working at the same number of units and he's going in the 200's when he was around 160's before the shot. It has lasted now for a week instead of the 48 hours I was told about and read about.   As soon as we were leaving from getting his vaccine, he started experiencing extreme fatigue.  That night and for 2 days he had a headache.  He is still more tired than usual and having to take naps.
LAB_DATA: I am trying to see if we can get some help/tests to determine if we should do the second dose or not but a nurse practitioner at the endocrinology department told me they recommend 2 doses because of what they have seen with COVID in the hospital but they just don't know enough about what the vaccine does to say it isn't hurting his honeymoon phase and to call the pediatrician's office because they know more about the vaccine and the nurse who called me back at the pediatrician's office referred me back to the endocrinology department to run tests.  The nurse practitioner said she'd talk to the doctor's.

On an unknown date, the outcome of the skin discoloration was recovered/resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the skin discoloration to be related to Shingrix. Two blood clots in the posterior lobes of her lung; heart rate was really fast; A spontaneous report was received from a 69 year-old female consumer who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced two blood clots in the posterior lobes of her lung and heart rate was really fast.   The patient's medical history included diverticulitis. Consumer mentioned that she was recovering from diverticulitis when she received the first Moderna vaccine.  Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included flagyl, bactrim, clindamycin (for a dental procedure one day after her vaccine), famotidine, lorazepam and elavil.  On 09 Feb 2021, four days prior to the onset of the events, the consumer received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: 030M20A) intramuscularly in left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 12 Feb 2021, the consumer experienced really fast heart rate and went to urgent care.  The patient was referred to the hospital where it was found that the patient had two blood clots in the posterior lobes of her lung and she was hospitalized. Treatment for the event included heparin bolus (dose and duration) not specified. The patient was discharged on 13 Feb 2021 and started on Eliquis 5 mg twice a day.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown.  The outcome of the events was resolved.  The assessment for the events was not provided.; Reporter's Comments: Very limited information regarding the events has been provided at this time.  Further information has been requested.
LAB_DATA: Test Date: 20210212; Test Name: Heart rate; Result Unstructured Data: Heart rate increased; Test Date: 20210309; Test Name: Heart rate; Result Unstructured Data: Heart rate increased

Adverse event resulted in Doctor or other healthcare professional office/clinic visit, Emergency room/department or urgent care. The outcome of events was not resolved. Treatment received for adverse event included OTC treatment with antihistamines; epinephrine (EPIPEN). No covid prior vaccination. No covid tested post vaccination.; Sender's Comments: A contributory role of vaccine BNT162B2 to the reported events rash and chills cannot be excluded based on the plausible temporal relationship and product safety profile. SYMPTOM_TEXT: When I got home around 5:30pm on Saturday I had a 5 minute coughing fit (dry cough) which seemed to come out of nowhere.  I was fine for the rest of the evening and when I woke up Sunday morning my arm was sore (from the shot) but I had no other side affects other than coughing occasionally.  I noticed my throat was raw.  I ran 3 miles, did my stretches and carried out my day without any apparent side effects.  I slept poorly but that is not that unusual, doing a full exercise routine Monday morning.  Other than the cough and raw throat, I seemed fine until the late afternoon (48 hour after the vaccination) when I started to ache all over--including a mild headache (which I rarely get) with the cough continuing and my throat raw.  I went to be early last night in the hopes that it would be over by morning, but it wasn't.  I still ache all over, including the headache, am still coughing a bit, my throat is still raw, and I feel completely dragged out.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 8 hrs after the second Moderna vaccination I starting having chills. These continued and increased in intensity along with the onset of fever. I did not have an accurate means of taking my temperature at the time. Over the course of the night on the 17th/18th of February the chills and fever never subsided, even with two doses of Tylenol. The day of the 18th, fever and chills continued along with a feeling of intense malaise. My sternum was very sore and it hurt to breathe as a result of the prolonged shivering. I had no appetite and ate absolutely nothing the day of the 18th. In the early morning hours of the 19th my fever broke as did the chills. However, later in the day, a thermometer was obtained and my fever was 101.4 degrees. When taken at bedtime, it was down the 99 degrees and returned to normal later with no future spikes. On the morning of the 20th when I awoke, I noticed a stinging soreness in my mouth and lip area, followed later in the day with my nostrils and inner nose. This turned out to be an intense outbreak of Herpes. The roof of my mouth, gums, upper surface of my tongue, lips, nostrils, and inner nose ultimately became covered and extremely painful. These lesions were not typical blebs, but were tiny, albeit most painful. After five days they resolved and I have had no further issues. As a possible area to investigate - I had had the second Shingles booster 14 days prior to my first Moderna COVID vaccination. I understand Shingles is also a Herpes family virus.
OTHER_MEDS: Doxazosin, Finasteride, Tadalafil, HCTZ, Atenolol, Lisinopril, Ezetimibe, Simvastatin, Carisoprodol, NORCO, Vitamin D3, CBD Oil

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received her first dose on 3/22/21 at approximately 1644. Patient states that she stayed at the clinic for 15 minutes (until 1700) but felt fine so she proceeded to the parking lot. Patient states that when she went into her car she started feeling as if she had an itchy throat; she states that at that time she was not very concerned until she brought it up to her husband and he encouraged her to go back inside to be evaluated. Patient arrived to nurse at approximately 1709, patient reported to nurse that she had tightness of throat but denied being unable to swallow. At 1711 oral Benadryl was administered. At this time patient was reporting being tachycardic and short of breath, nurse assessed her oxygenation status, which was at 99%, and her heart rate was at 104. Nurse encouraged patient to deep breath and try to relax. At 1718 Patient reported that her tightness was getting worst, it was getting more difficult for her to swallow. At this time, this nurse collaborated with another nurse for course of action of which we decided to administer 0.5 mg of epinephrine and call 9-1-1. At 1720 Epinephrine was administered intramuscular into the right deltoid. Patient at this time stated that her tightness had expanded into her chest and was progressively getting worst. At 1724 Lung sounds at this time were still clear and her oxygenation status was 99% with heart rate of 125. At 1725 EMS personnel took over care for the patient, after they further assessed they made the decision to transfer the patient to a nearby hospital for further evaluation. At approximately 1729 emergency personnel wheeled out patient on a stretcher.
ALLERGIES: Patient reported she allergic to several medications and food products

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Had vaccine and a couple of hours later was very sore at the injection site, and then was very sore the following day and then continued to a lesser extent until 3/11/21.  On 3/6/21 she woke up and had chills, extreme fatigue, no appetite, was kind of wobbly and she slept almost 24 hours.  It was an effort to chew.  Then that evening there was a very faint rash slightly over her shoulder of the same arm, it was not oval, kind of more irregular shaped and was not really itchy.  Then on 3/8/21 for about 1/4" to 1/2" there was a faint pink circle around the injection site and the rest of the rash had traveled down the arm to about 1/2 the size it was before and the underside of the arm/armpit was sore.  She could not tell if there were swollen glands or not.  The very faint rash went until the 9th.  The chills went through until 3/12/21, but the rest of the symptoms were much less, but the fatigue went until about the 12th. There was runny nose and congestion that started on 3/9, and went to 3/15/21, and the chills then restarted again on 3/15/21.  She also had a scratchy throat from 3/12 - 3/15/21.  She could barely function the first 3 days, just pretty much slept all the time the first week.
OTHER_MEDS: Centrum silver, magnesium, Vitamin B12, calcium +D3.
PRIOR_VAX: To vaccine #1 above.
ALLERGIES: Possibly Ibuprofen.  Mold, dust, pollen, ingredient in soap/perfume/eye makeup.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: In November of 2020 I was diagnosed with COVID 19 and subsequently recovered.  This was my first Moderna shot.  I took the shot in the right arm and completed my work day with no side effects.  I went to the gym that night - as usual - and wanted to "work that arm" a little.  I had a good workout, no issues.  Went home, ate and went to bed.  About 1 or 2 am I woke up with the hottest raging inferno flu-like fever I can recall having as an adult.  I did not want to alert my wife, so I simply stayed in bed and did not measure my fever level.  My guess is it was >102.  Fever continued until a.m. and deep body pain hit me.  At dawn my fever measured 101.  I took acetaminophen and took a cold shower.  Fever subsided for a short while.  Then it came  back.  I felt weak and flu-pain so I stayed home from work and simply slept it off.  Symptoms slowly subsided by 7pm day 2.  Day 3 I was not 100% but I went to work and was fine.  No other symptoms since.
OTHER_MEDS: Levothyroxyin, vitamin d, fish oil, blood pressure med and cholesterol med

Got the vaccine, on the first day within the first hour she started feeling itchy, tingling sensation above her eyebrow over the left eye.  Didn't stay long, but sensation of itching left her.  Then noticed a pin dot of a little red spot on the left side of the eye, temple area, itchy and then it went away.  That night the soreness started in the arm.  The next day the whole arm was sore, but she kept exercising it and moving it.  On the third day the arm was clearing up like she didn't get a shot.  Then, the left thigh had some achiness.  The right ankle was achy as well, didn't stay long.  She is still waking up with a rapid heart beat.  She has a FU APT for labs and revisit with her PCP in a month.    On Saturday, 3/20/17 and woke up with heart palpitations, which they continued until she went to the ER around 4:00 AM.  They checked her, did an EKG, ran labs and VS.  The labs came back and told her that her potassium was depleted, and gave her something to calm her down.  She went to the store on Sunday and got some potassium citrate to maintain herself until she could get to the Doctor on Monday.  They did give her potassium while she was in the ER.  She went to the doctor on Monday, and he started her on a prescription for potassium.  She also made an appointment with her nephrologist to make sure she was okay before she gets the 2nd vaccine since she only has one kidney.  She also has had a lot of bruising from the blood draws in the hospital.
LAB_DATA: Lab work that showed depleted potassium.    EKG that was normal.
PRIOR_VAX: Childhood vaccines, always got the measles, mumps, etc. from the vaccines.

It was unknown if the reporter considered the pain in arm to be related to Shingrix.  Additional information was provided as follows: The age at vaccination was not reported. The patient received Shingrix injection a couple of years before reporting and experienced sore arm. The patient received unspecified BioNTech COVID Vaccine. The patient got the Pfizer vaccine and was getting the second one on 21st February 2021. They did not get her the vaccine card. She just knew it was Pfizer BioNTech COVID vaccine. The unusual side effects she experienced were deep fissures in her tongue, sensitivity in her tongue, and sensitive pallet. She had a reddish sensitive pallet. She was spitting blood for 4 hours before she realized she had fissures in the tongue. She could not contribute it to anything except she had the vaccination. She noticed it 3 nights after the vaccine. The fissures could have been developing, but she did not examine it until it started bleeding. Her tongue was examined frequently during the year by her dentist and her doctor. She got the vaccine on 31st January 2021. The symptoms could have started between 31st January 2021 and she noticed the bleeding on 3rd February 2021. It was before six or so when she got the injection and she was spitting blood about 6PM on 3rd February 2021. The bleeding lasted for 4 hours and she was about to go to emergency room , but the bleeding stopped. She had not bled again. The fissures were not cleared. The entire tongue had groves they were deep. There were still fissures there. Her pallet was still sensitive but it was not bleeding. It was red and the doctor told to use a Q-tip to apply hydrogen peroxide. That was all she suggested. Some days the fissures seem more irritated. Her dentist looks at her tongue closely twice a year. She saw the dentist in December and saw her primary care doctor in January. All labs were good. She hopes this did not happen with the second dose. She would say her tongue was slightly swollen. It was not preventing her from breathing, but the swelling was from the fissures. She get rashes from medications. She did not take the medications anymore.  The reporter consented to follow up. For tolerance of 2nd dose of shingrix, refer case US2021AMR045165.; Sender's Comments:  US-GLAXOSMITHKLINE-US2021AMR045165:same patient

SYMPTOM_TEXT: expired dose of Act-HIB given, stated that on the component or powder it say 29-May-2021 and the dilute stated 01-Mar-2021 with no reported adverse event; Initial information received on 04-Mar-2021 regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case received from a physician and consumer/ non health care professional.  This case involves a 3 year-old female patient who was vaccinated with expired dose of HIB (PRP/T) VACCINE [ACT-HIB], stated that on the component or powder would expired on 29-may-2021 and the dilute expired on 01-Mar-2021 (Expired Product administered).   The patient's past medical history, medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided.  Concomitant medications included DIPHTHERIA VACCINE TOXOID, PERTUSSIS VACCINE ACELLULAR, TETANUS VACCINE TOXOID (DAPTACEL) for prophylactic vaccination.  On 03-Mar-2021, the patient received 0.5 mL (once) dose of suspect HIB (PRP/T) VACCINE (strength- standard) [lot UJ165AAA and expiry date 01-Mar-2021) via intramuscular/right vastuslaterallus route in unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination.  It was a case of actual medication error due to expired vaccine used (latency was on same day).  At the time of report, patient had no adverse event.  This suspected adverse reaction report is submitted and classified as a medication error solely and exclusively to ensure the marketing authorization holder's compliance with the requirements set out in Directive 2001/83/EC and Module VI of the Good Pharmacovigilance Practices. I've lost 16 pounds in 1 month and 20 days without trying.  Moderna killed my obsession for food.  I was 268 lbs when I presented for the 1st dose of Moderna at the Robeson CRV.  Within 24 hours I was weak, cold, aching all over, and nauseous. The nausea moved over to lack of interest in food.     I've struggled with intense craving for food non-stop for 30 years.  The cravings are gone.  By my second shot in March I was down to around 260 lbs.  Twenty days after my second shot, I am down to 252lbs.  Food is more of a necessity now rather than a constant desire.  I believe the vaccine modulated insulin/ghrelin or crossed the blood brain barrier and modulated the incessant dopamine reward signaling in the mesolimbic DA pathway when I eat food.  I reach satiety easily now.  I also have diminished need for Ativan.  I use to drink close to a gallon of water a day.  Now I have no real interest.  I might drink a couple liters a day.  To put things in perspective, before Moderna, I could eat 2 foot long Subway sandwiches, 3-6 cookies, 2-4 32 oz of soda and chips to stop my hunger for 2-3 hours.  2-3 hours later I would feel extremely hungry with a growling stomach. I could then consume 2-3 double cheeseburgers, a 20 piece nugget, 2 parfaits, and a chocolate sundae.  After Moderna, now a half a Subway sandwich and maybe a cookie are enough to last for most of the day.  The desire for food has diminished to necessity to eat and lack of interest in eating, even when my stomach is empty.  If I have a soda or sparkling water, I might have 1 or 2 and stop.  Moderna flipped some hormonal switch in my body.  It's great.  Food went from being an insatiable desire to a basic necessity.  I've lost 16 pounds in 1 month and 20 days without trying.
OTHER_MEDS: Zoloft, Ativan, Gabapentin, Buspar, Lopressor  Synthroid, Testosterone Cypionate
HISTORY: Obesity, hyperlipidemia, hypertension, hypogonadism, anxiety, depression, PTSD, reflux.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vaccine admin. At 8:38 am at Vaccine Clinic.  The nurse (I?ve forgotten her name - boomer aged, short gray hair) was standing when she administered the vaccine, and I remember making a note of the whole situation because it was the first time that a nurse did NOT say, ?Relax your arm.? I thought that was odd.  I felt nauseous and dizzy within 1-2 min., but after my 15 min. Waiting period was up, I was no longer feeling dizzy or nauseous so I left. Within 10 min.  I felt an ache in my arm, deep in the bone, and different then the regular shot-site pain.  This is a dull ache that is barely tolerable.  A few hours later, my shoulders and neck were experiencing very extreme, sharp pain, and I can barely move my arm, neck, and head.  It hurts to hold my head up straight.  This pain continues for another 2 days. It is a very intense, throbbing ache, and worse after a fitful night of rest, due to the constant pain in my left arm and neck.  48 hours later, still in intense pain and got a massage.  Helped briefly but pain returned within minutes.  On day 3, I got another more targeted massage on my shoulders and neck, with only a brief amount of time free from the pain.  Day 4, the pain is so intense and I can barely handle it. I make an appointment with a APRN. She does not mention SIRVA but prescribes 800mg of Ibuprofen every 4 hours as needed for pain, and Flexeril, a muscle relaxer. She also gave me a shot of Toradol for the pain.  The Flexeril makes me drowsy, and the ibuprofen takes the sharp edge of the pain away, but does nothing to mask the dull, deep ache in my left arm and shoulder.  Day 5, 6, 7 all the same.  On day 7, a new tingling sensation and numbness in my left hand and fingers start.  Contacted office again to request a referral for physical therapy, and also to make a note of SIRVA in my file. Got a prescription for a stronger pain medication; neurontin to hopefully make the pain more manageable.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received Pfizer COVID 19 vaccine at 8:42am. This was patient's first dose. He was observed in clinic for 18 minutes afterwards without concern and left approximately 9:00am. Patient returned to clinic at 9:28am with complaints of sweating, nausea and lightheadedness. RN took patient to private observation room and started assessment. VS 9:30am O2 100%, BP 147/78, HR 50. Patient is laid back on bed with head at 45 degrees and legs elevated. Patient was given 6oz of water and neurological assessment completed. Patient alert and oriented without changes. Patient denies SOB, scratchy or tight throat, hoarse voice, trouble swallowing or itching. VS 9:40am O2 100%, BP 151/77, HR 54. Patient given another 6 oz of water and continues to lie back with feet elevated. Patient took clonidine, sertraline, propranolol, Adderall and vraylar this AM. He ate breakfast. Is not a diabetic. Patient states his lightheadedness has subsided, still complains of sweating and nausea but states he is "feeling better and ready to go home". Patient has a ride and is going home to his parent's house where they will both stay with him all day. VS 9:45 O2 100%, BP 143/81, HR 61. Patient appears more comfortable, less anxious and HR has risen. States his nausea is lessening. Patient would like to leave. RN educated patient on emergency signs to seek 911 for and they include SOB, throat swelling, sudden emesis, increased lightheadedness or nausea, fainting, new dizziness or any other sudden change in condition. He voices understanding; plans to go home with parents, have toast for lunch, push fluids and rest. Patient escorted to the door and visualized entering vehicle with family.
HISTORY: OSA, GERD, Tobacco use disorder, hx of heroin use

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Brain encephalopathy; This spontaneous report was received from a consumer (daughter) concerning an 89 year-old female patient who was administered Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and developed  brain encephalopathy (encephalopathy).  The patient's medical history included aortic aneurysm (untreated), esophageal hernia (repaired), rectal cancer and uterine cancer. Concomitant medications included lisinopril, furosemide, sertraline, levothyroxine and FDgard.  On 21-Jan-2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot/Batch number: 032L20A). On 17-Feb-2021, the patient received their second dose of mRNA-1273 (Batch/Lot # 006M20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 08-Feb-2021, 13 days after first vaccination, the family started to notice small balance changes, slight fine motor coordination changes (handwriting, etc.) and a little forgetfulness. They chalked it up to her being an 89 year-old. On 17-Feb-2021, the patient was administered her second dose of the vaccine. On an unknown date, the patient was unable to stand without assistance, leans backwards when trying to stand, has developed a spastic tremor bilaterally in her arms and her cognition is completely altered. She is experiencing hallucinations, memory loss, can follow some directions and her speech is clear, but inappropriate. Her hand writing was concise and clear prior to vaccine, but later became illegible; missing entries with no spatial awareness. On an unknown date, she was hospitalized. On 06-Mar-2021 and 07-Mar-2021 a CT (computed tomography) of brain, CT of neck, multiple urinalysis and multiple blood labs were performed. On 07-Mar-2021, the patient could not identify immediate family members in a photo. On 8-Mar-2021, short EEG (electroencephalogram), brain CTs with and without contrast, neurological consultation, speech consultation, psychological evaluation, lumbar puncture and MRI (magnetic resonance imaging) were performed. Results are pending. She has been diagnosed with brain encephalopathy, probably caused by molecular mimicry in response to the vaccine. She is being treated, but treatment information was not provided. The patient's daughter reports that prior to the vaccination, her mother was fully independent, living alone, mobile and with excellent cognitive function.    Action taken with the drug in response to the event is not applicable.  The outcome for the event, brain encephalopathy, was not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Drug allergy; Esophageal hernia (Repaired); Rectal cancer; Uterine cancer

Hospital Discharge Summary Note: Patient is a 73-year-old female with a past medical history significant for hypertension, hyperlipidemia, hypothyroidism, and breast cancer.  She presented to the emergency department with reports of possible allergic reaction to Pfizer vaccine.  Patient received her first dose of: Vaccine earlier today and approximately 5 minutes later developed a cough, diaphoresis, and lightheadedness.  She was given 50 mg oral Benadryl in the ED.  Patient then complained of tingling sensation throughout her body and was continuously coughing.  She was brought to the emergency department for evaluation.  Patient noted she felt jittery and "disconnected".  In the ED her cough and dizziness significantly improved.  Upon examination, patient was noted to have right lower extremity weakness.  She denied any weakness.  CT of the head was performed to rule out stroke.  Neurology was consulted.   CT head brain was negative however patient was still having right-sided weakness.  Emergency department physician confirmed the patient was able to get up without difficulty after receiving her vaccine at 1415 immediately following her vaccine.  It was determined she was within the window for TPA.  Patient was transferred to the ICU for further management.

Received Pfizer 2nd dose vaccine on 01/20/2021 at 7:00 AM in the patient's right arm - around 5:00 PM the same day, the patient's knees started feeling wobbly, worse on left than the right. Knees continued to swell with limited motion, discomfort on bending, no point tenderness, and a negative meniscal exam. Swelling was worse on the left. X-ray normal. Worsening symptoms continued that limited standing and walking. Labs done on 2/2/2021 came back positive for Lyme disease and reactive arthritis. Swelling initially improved when patient was put on doxycycline, but worsened significantly after physical use. MRI showed large effusion in the left knee consistent with Lyme and a small focal lateral posterior horn meniscal tear not consistent with effusion. Effusion was drained March 1st and was PCR positive for spirochetes. WBC in effusion was 3400. Patient switched to amoxicillin and knee showed improvement by March 12th, 2021.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I visited my doctor. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 40 minutes after receiving the second COVID19 vaccination, my heart began racing, I was lightheaded, and my tongue began to swell.  I was taken to an observation room, and a my oxygen saturation was checked.  Because my tongue continued to swell, my chest felt tight, and breathing became shallow, I was injected with 50mg of Benadryl.  I asked for this instead of the Epi pen injection.   The constriction in my chest improved a bit and my tongue started to reduce in size.  I was very sleepy and had the shivers.  After a half hour of resting, I was driven home by family.  The next day I had terrible joint pain, fatigue and chills.  Breathing was fine, but I was easily exhausted by any exertion.  Starting the third day, I was at work teaching and noticed a rapid heart rate, increased chest tightness and extreme fatigue from talking or walking the stairs.  The fourth day I had to leave work early because of the lack of breath and fatigue.  I visited my family doctor who gave me Prednisone and a rescue inhaler, and I started taking the medication. The fifth day my symptoms were the same, but I sat at my desk and was able to do paperwork.  The sixth and seventh days I had to get a substitute for my job, as I did not have enough energy or breath to teach or walk the stairs at school.  I have been on vacation from work since Saturday, a full seven days after the vaccination, and continue to have extreme fatigue and chest tightness with any exertion.   Sunday night I went to the Emergency because I could not get a deep breath and felt like I was suffocating. My oxygen levels were high and my blood pressure good, but the muscles in my neck and chest were constricted making me gasp and choke on my spit.  I was given an albuterol treatment and an anti anxiety drug to help relax me so I could breath normally.  I am still struggling with these symptoms of tight chest, constricted breathing, and extreme fatigue.  But now I am sleeping sitting upright and afraid to fall asleep because I may not be able to breath.
OTHER_MEDS: Turmeric Mood support Adrenal B vitamins Conjugated Linoleic acid
HISTORY: tight musculature, prone to muscle spasms

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She got the vaccine, everything was fine, they warned her about being sick.  She did not have any reaction at all until she woke up 13 days later on 3/5/2021 and her left eye was blind.  She had some sort of blob that changes colors and moves around.  It sometimes is orange.  She knew she did not have macular degeneration as it centers it.  Sometimes it sparkles and has grain to it.  He said that she had an arterial blood, and that leaked from the carotid artery into the eye has not completely sealed off.  She can see out of the right eye perfectly, but she cannot see a little out of the left eye.  If she's watching the TV she can see the top of the newscasters hair, but she cannot see anything below that.  Her vision is upward either, can see out of either side, but cannot below horizontal down.  He told her that it was basically a stroke that didn't reach her brain and went to her eye.  He told her to return to see him (ophthalmologist) on 5/18/21 at 10:00 AM.  She also is to see her PCP on 5/20/21.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 10 min. after pt. received the vaccine she began to wheeze. She used her own Albuterol MDI. There was no improvement. She repeated the MDI 5 min. later. Her chest got tighter and wheezing increased. Pt. taken to treatment room and 911 called . Pt. given 25mg Benadryl by MD who is on site at vaccine clinic. At 0955, pt. given 0.3ml epi. in right upper arm. At 9:57 pt administered 2 more puff of Albuterol. On exam: HR 92, BP 138/82. EMS arrived 10:10, IV access obtained, dexamethasone pushed,  and albuterol neb started. On transfer BP 144/80, pulse 85 and o2 sat 100%. Pt. remained awake and alert. Wheezing improving on transport at 10:20.   Notes provided by Dr.
Small painless dry rash on top of right hand. Appeared morning after vaccine. Has faded throughout the day.  Itchy throat and headache.

Four hours after receiving the first dose I experienced  substantial swelling , redness, heat, and a very heavy upper left arm. I was unable to sleep on that side for a week. The redness , swelling and heat lasted 14 days. My doctor looked at my arm on day 11 , and was surprised seeing the bright redness and feeling the heat 11 days after vaccination. The full healing  finally occurred on day 15. Hence  I opted not to get the second dose since the reaction might be far greater.

First episode 2/21 [26 hours after 2nd shot].  Dull Chest pain.  Took 2 Tylenol and it went away.  Eleven days later,  chest pain returns but pain radiates up back into neck and head.  Took 2 Tylenol and went to bed.   Pain subsides.  Next 3 days pain repeats from chest to  head.  Fourth day I start to shiver internally.  This lasted about 75 minutes before going away..  Next day went to ER.  All ER tests were negative and was released.  Went to cardiologist and had a stress test and several other tests that were all normal.   A week later, I thought I was having a heart attack and went back to ER.  All tests were negative again.  Still wake up with neck pain  alleviated with Tylenol..
LAB_DATA: EKG, echocardiogram, Chest MRI w/ contrast, stress test and  heart enzymes all normal.
